Name: Price % of 200 Day Moving Avg
Description: The current stock price expressed as a percentage of the 200 day moving average.

Name: Price % of 50 Day Moving Avg
Description: The current stock price expressed as a percentage of the 50 day moving average.

Name: Price % of 52 Week High
Description: The current stock price expressed as a percentage of the 52 week high.

Name: Price % of 52 Week Low
Description: The current stock price expressed as a percentage of the 52 week low.

Name: 52 Week High
Description: The highest trade price over the last year adjusted for stock splits.

Name: 52 Week Low
Description: The lowest trade price over the last year adjusted for stock splits.

Name: 52 Week High (Div & Split Adjusted)
Description: The highest trade price over the last year adjusted for stock splits and dividends.

Name: 52 Week Low (Div & Split Adjusted)
Description: The lowest trade price over the last year adjusted for stock splits and dividends.

Name: YTD Stock Price Total Return
Description: The total change in stock price, adjusted for splits, so far this calendar year.

Name: 1 Day Stock Price Total Return
Description: The total change in stock price (adjusted of dividends and splits) over the prior close price.

Name: 1 Week Stock Price Total Return
Description: The total change in stock price (adjusted of dividends and splits) over the last 1 week.

Name: 2 Week Stock Price Total Return
Description: The total change in stock price (adjusted of dividends and splits) over the last 2 weeks.

Name: 3 Week Stock Price Total Return
Description: The total change in stock price (adjusted of dividends and splits) over the last 3 weeks.

Name: 4 Week Stock Price Total Return
Description: The total change in stock price (adjusted of dividends and splits) over the last 4 weeks.

Name: 1 Month Stock Price Total Return
Description: The total change in stock price (adjusted of dividends and splits) over the last 1 month.

Name: 3 Month Stock Price Total Return
Description: The total change in stock price (adjusted of dividends and splits) over the last 3 months.

Name: 6 Month Stock Price Total Return
Description: The total change in stock price (adjusted of dividends and splits) over the last 6 months.

Name: 9 Month Stock Price Total Return
Description: The total change in stock price (adjusted of dividends and splits) over the last 9 months.

Name: 1 Year Stock Price Total Return
Description: The total change in stock price (adjusted of dividends and splits) over the last 1 year.

Name: 2 Year Stock Price Total Return
Description: The total change in stock price (adjusted of dividends and splits) over the last 2 years.

Name: 3 Year Stock Price Total Return
Description: The total change in stock price (adjusted of dividends and splits) over the last 3 years.

Name: 4 Year Stock Price Total Return
Description: The total change in stock price (adjusted of dividends and splits) over the last 4 years.

Name: 5 Year Stock Price Total Return
Description: The total change in stock price (adjusted of dividends and splits) over the last 5 years.

Name: 7 Year Stock Price Total Return
Description: The total change in stock price (adjusted of dividends and splits) over the last 7 years.

Name: 10 Year Stock Price Total Return
Description: The total change in stock price (adjusted of dividends and splits) over the last 10 years.

Name: 5 Day Moving Avg
Description: The average stock price over the last 5 trading days.

Name: 10 Day Moving Avg
Description: The average stock price over the last 10 trading days.

Name: 20 Day Moving Avg
Description: The average stock price over the last 20 trading days.

Name: 50 Day Moving Avg
Description: The average stock price over the last 50 trading days.

Name: 200 Day Moving Avg
Description: The average stock price over the last 200 trading days.

Name: 255 Day Moving Avg
Description: The average stock price over the last 255 trading days.

Name: Accounts Payable
Description: Amounts payable to vendors extended as a line of credit for normal business purchases.

Name: Accounts Receivable, Net
Description: The total amount of collectibles for a company net of receivables that are deemed to be uncollectible.

Name: Accounts Receivable, Gross
Description: The total amount of collectibles for a company.

Name: Accrued Expenses (Bank)
Description: Metric adjusted for considerations applicable to structure and operations of banks.

Name: Accrued Expenses
Description: Expenses that have been incurred but not paid.

Name: Accrued Interest Payable
Description: This item represents the amount of interest accrued in the accounts of banks in respect of interest payable to its customers on its deposits.

Name: Accrued Interest Receivable
Description: This item represents interest accrued (i.e. earned but not yet due) on loans, securities, certificates of deposit, or other investments. This item is available only in Banks and Thrifts.

Name: Accumulated Allowance for Doubtful Accounts
Description: The calculated value of receivables that are deemed to be uncollectible.

Name: Accumulated Depreciation
Description:
This item represents the year-end accumulated balance of amounts provided as depreciation 
on property, plant and equipment till the current year.

Name: Additional Paid In Capital
Description: The excess over par value paid for common securities.

Name: Adjusted Funds from Operations
Description: Funds from operations (FFO) with adjustments made for recurring capital expenditures used to maintain the underlying assets. Typically used to evaluate REITs.

Name: Adjusted Funds From Operations Growth
Description: Period over prior period growth in adjusted funds from operations (AFFO).

Name: Adjusted Funds From Operations Margin
Description: Adjusted funds from operations (AFFO) expressed as a percent of revenue.

Name: Advertising Expense
Description: This item represents expenditure incurred towards advertising, marketing, promotional and publicity. This data item is extracted for 10Ks only.

Name: AFFO / Share Forecast Consensus Standard Deviation
Description: The median AFFO / share Forecast submitted by any analyst for the company.

Name: AFFO / Share Forecast Count of Estimates
Description: Standard deviation in forecasted AFFO / share.

Name: AFFO / Share Forecast High Consensus
Description: The number of analysts publishing a AFFO / share Forecast for the stock.

Name: AFFO / Share Forecast Low Consensus
Description: The highest AFFO / share Forecast submitted by any analyst for the company.

Name: AFFO / Share Forecast Mean Consensus
Description: The lowest AFFO / share Forecast submitted by any analyst for the company.

Name: AFFO / Share Forecast Median Consensus
Description: The mean or average AFFO / share Forecast submitted by any analyst for the company.

Name: AFFO Forecast
Description: Projected adjusted funds from operations for the company.

Name: AFFO Forecast CAGR (10y)
Description: Ten year compound annual growth rate in forecasted adjusted funds from operations.

Name: AFFO Forecast CAGR (5y)
Description: Five year compound annual growth rate in forecasted adjusted funds from operations.

Name: AFFO Forecast Consensus Standard Deviation
Description: Standard deviation in forecasted adjusted funds from operations.

Name: AFFO Forecast Count of Estimates
Description: The number of analysts publishing a AFFO Forecast for the stock.

Name: AFFO Forecast High Consensus
Description: The highest AFFO Forecast submitted by any analyst for the company.

Name: AFFO Forecast Low Consensus
Description: The lowest AFFO Forecast submitted by any analyst for the company.

Name: AFFO Forecast Mean Consensus
Description: The mean or average AFFO Forecast submitted by any analyst for the company.

Name: AFFO Forecast Median Consensus
Description: The median AFFO Forecast submitted by any analyst for the company.

Name: AFFO Growth Forecast
Description: Period over prior period growth in forecasted adjusted funds from operations.

Name: AFFO Margin Forecast
Description: Forecasted adjusted funds from operations as a percent of forecasted revenue.

Name: AFFO Yield (Adjusted Funds From Operations)
Description: Funds from operations (FFO) with adjustments made for recurring capital expenditures used to maintain the underlying assets. Typically used to evaluate REITs.

Name: Allowance for Loan Losses
Description: This item represents allowance for loan losses, which are provided to absorb possible future losses from loans. The allowances are made after a review of the recoverability of the loans made. This item is available only for banks. This item includes 1. Allowance for loan losses and 2. Valuation allowance. This item excludes 1. Undisbursed portion of loans in process, 2. Unearned premiums, 3. Unearned discounts, 4. Net Deferred Loan Origination Fees, and 5. Documented Interest.

Name: Altman Z-Score
Description: A formula used to predict the probability that a firm will go into bankruptcy within two years.

Name: Amort. Of Goodwill & Intangible Assets (Bank)
Description: This item represents the periodic write-off of intangible assets like patents, trademarks, copyrights, software rights etc, reported by the company in Income statement. This item may include the portion attributable to amortization of goodwill also, when the company reports both amortisation of goodwill and intangibles in a combined line item.

Name: Amort. Of Goodwill & Intangible Assets (Insurance)
Description: This item represents the amortization expense related to Goodwill and Intangible Assets.

Name: Amortization of Deferred Charges (CF)
Description: This item represents both amortization and write-off of deferred expenses. Deferred charges result from prepayment of expenses of capital nature (not represented by tangible assets) whose benefit, usually will extend over a period of years from the time of incurrence and so is carried forward for expensing in future years.

Name: Amortization Of Film Costs
Description: This item represents amortization of costs incurred for film production. This type of expenditure is very common for companies which are in film production and media businesses.

Name: Analyst Price Target Count
Description: The number of analyst price targets tracked for a stock. Price targets represent what analysts believe a stock will be worth within the next 12 to 18 months.

Name: Analyst Price Target High
Description: The highest analyst price target for a stock. Price targets represent what analysts believe a stock will be worth within the next 12 to 18 months.

Name: Analyst Price Target Low
Description: The lowest analyst price target for a stock. Price targets represent what analysts believe a stock will be worth within the next 12 to 18 months.

Name: Analyst Price Target Mean
Description: The mean or average analyst price target for a stock. Price targets represent what analysts believe a stock will be worth within the next 12 to 18 months.

Name: Analyst Price Target Median
Description: The median analyst price target for a stock. Price targets represent what analysts believe a stock will be worth within the next 12 to 18 months.

Name: Analyst Price Target Standard Deviation
Description: The standard deviation in the analyst price targets for a stock. Price targets represent what analysts believe a stock will be worth within the next 12 to 18 months.

Name: Announcement Date of Last Dividend
Description: Announcement date of the last dividend.

Name: As Reported, Revenue
Description: This item represents the total revenues as reported by the company in its financial statement. This data item is available only when the company reports total revenues.

Name: As Reported, Operating Income
Description: This item represents the operating income or operating profit as reported by the company in its financial statement.

Name: Asset Efficiency
Description: A ratio that measures the amount of cash flow that a company generates from its assets.

Name: Asset Management Fee
Description: This item represents the fees earned from managing the assets of third party. Also includes fees earned on providing banking services like check writing, credit cards and debit cards, brokerage features like buying securities and making loans on margin & the convenience of having all financial transactions listed on one monthly statement.

Name: Asset Turnover
Description: A ratio that measures the dollars in revenue a company generates per dollar of assets.

Name: Asset Writedown
Description: An expense incurred when the carrying value of an asset is greater than its fair value and it is written down or decreased in value to equal its current fair value.

Name: Assets of Discontinued Operations, Current
Description: The aggregate value of current assets from business segments that a company has disposed of or wants to dispose of in the near future.

Name: Assets of Discontinued Operations, Long-term
Description: The aggregate value of non-current assets from business segments that a company has disposed of or wants to dispose of in the near future.

Name: Assets on Oper. Lease, Accum. Depr.
Description: This item represents the closing i.e. year-end accumulated balances of amounts provided as depreciation over the life of the assets given by the company on operating leases to others, till the end of the current year.

Name: Assets on Oper. Lease, Gross
Description: This item represents the Assets of a durable nature i.e. property, plant and equipment, at their gross values, which are given by the company on operating leases to others rather than being used in the production or sale of goods.

Name: Assets Under Cap. Lease, Accum. Depr.
Description: This item represents the closing i.e. year-end accumulated balances of amounts provided as depreciation over the life of the assets taken by the company on capital leases from others, till the end of the current year.

Name: Average Assets
Description: Average of beginning and ending bank asset balances.

Name: Average Daily Dollar Volume (3m)
Description: The three-month average of shares traded each day multiplied by the stock price.

Name: Average Daily Volume (3m)
Description: The three-month average of shares traded each day.

Name: Average Loans
Description: Average of beginning and ending bank loan balances.

Name: Avg AFFO Margin Forecast (10y)
Description: Ten year average forecasted adjusted funds from operations (AFFO) margin.

Name: Avg AFFO Margin Forecast (5y)
Description: Five year average forecasted adjusted funds from operations (AFFO) margin.

Name: Avg Book / Market (10y)
Description: Ten-year quarterly average Book / Market.

Name: Avg Book / Market (5y)
Description: Five-year quarterly average Book / Market.

Name: Avg Capital Expenditures Margin (10y)
Description: Ten-year quarterly average capital expenditures margin.

Name: Avg Capital Expenditures Margin (5y)
Description: Five-year quarterly average capital expenditures margin.

Name: Avg EBIT Margin (10y)
Description: Ten-year quarterly average EBIT margin.

Name: Avg EBIT Margin (5y)
Description: Five-year quarterly average EBIT margin.

Name: Avg EBIT Margin Forecast (10y)
Description: Ten year average forecasted earnings before interest and taxes (EBIT) margin.

Name: Avg EBIT Margin Forecast (5y)
Description: Five year average forecasted earnings before interest and taxes (EBIT) margin.

Name: Avg EBITDA Margin (10y)
Description: Ten-year quarterly average EBITDA margin.

Name: Avg EBITDA Margin (5y)
Description: Five-year quarterly average EBITDA margin.

Name: Avg EBITDA Margin Forecast (10y)
Description: Ten year average forecasted earnings before interest, taxes, depreciation and amortization (EBITDA) margin.

Name: Avg EBITDA Margin Forecast (5y)
Description: Five year average forecasted earnings before interest, taxes, depreciation and amortization (EBITDA) margin.

Name: Avg EV / EBIT (10y)
Description: Ten-year quarterly average EV / EBIT.

Name: Avg EV / EBIT (5y)
Description: Five-year quarterly average EV / EBIT.

Name: Avg EV / EBITDA (10y)
Description: Ten-year quarterly average EV / EBITDA.

Name: Avg EV / EBITDA (5y)
Description: Five-year quarterly average EV / EBITDA.

Name: Avg EV / Revenue (10y)
Description: Ten-year quarterly average EV / Revenue.

Name: Avg EV / Revenue (5y)
Description: Five-year quarterly average EV / Revenue.

Name: Avg FCF Yield (10y)
Description: Ten-year quarterly average FCF Yield.

Name: Avg FCF Yield (5y)
Description: Five-year quarterly average FCF Yield.

Name: Avg FFO Margin Forecast (10y)
Description: Ten year average forecasted funds from operations (AFFO) margin.

Name: Avg FFO Margin Forecast (5y)
Description: Five year average forecasted funds from operations (AFFO) margin.

Name: Avg Gross Profit Margin (10y)
Description: Ten-year quarterly average gross profit margin.

Name: Avg Gross Profit Margin (5y)
Description: Five-year quarterly average gross profit margin.

Name: Avg Net Income Margin Forecast (10y)
Description: Ten year average forecasted net income margin.

Name: Avg Net Income Margin Forecast (5y)
Description: Five year average forecasted net income margin.

Name: Avg Net Income to Stockholders Margin (10y)
Description: Ten-year quarterly average net profit margin.

Name: Avg Net Income to Stockholders Margin (5y)
Description: Five-year quarterly average net profit margin.

Name: Avg NOPAT Margin Forecast (10y)
Description: Ten year average forecasted net operating profit after tax margin.

Name: Avg NOPAT Margin Forecast (5y)
Description: Five year average forecasted net operating profit after tax margin.

Name: Avg Operating Income Margin (10y)
Description: Ten-year quarterly average operating income margin.

Name: Avg Operating Income Margin (5y)
Description: Five-year quarterly average operating income margin.

Name: Avg P/E Ratio (10y)
Description: Ten-year quarterly average P/E ratio.

Name: Avg P/E Ratio (5y)
Description: Five-year quarterly average P/E ratio.

Name: Avg P/E Ratio (Adjusted) (10y)
Description: Ten-year quarterly average P/E ratio (adjusted).

Name: Avg P/E Ratio (Adjusted) (5y)
Description: Five-year quarterly average P/E ratio (adjusted).

Name: Avg Price / Book (10y)
Description: Ten-year quarterly average Price / Book.

Name: Avg Price / Book (5y)
Description: Five-year quarterly average Price / Book.

Name: Avg Price / LTM Sales (10y)
Description: Ten-year quarterly average Price / LTM Sales.

Name: Avg Price / LTM Sales (5y)
Description: Five-year quarterly average Price / LTM Sales.

Name: Avg Return on Assets (10y)
Description: Ten-year quarterly average return on assets.

Name: Avg Return on Assets (5y)
Description: Five-year quarterly average return on assets.

Name: Avg Return on Common Equity (10y)
Description: Ten-year quarterly average return on common equity.

Name: Avg Return on Common Equity (5y)
Description: Five-year quarterly average return on common equity.

Name: Avg Return on Invested Capital (10y)
Description: Ten-year quarterly average return on invested capital.

Name: Avg Return on Invested Capital (5y)
Description: Five-year quarterly average return on invested capital.

Name: Avg Unlevered FCF Margin Forecast (10y)
Description: Ten year average forecasted unlevered free cash flow margin.

Name: Avg Unlevered FCF Margin Forecast (5y)
Description: Five year average forecasted unlevered free cash flow margin.

Name: Basic EPS (Cont. Ops)
Description: Company's net earnings or losses from continuing operations on a per basic share basis.

Name: Basic EPS (Cont. Ops) CAGR (10y)
Description: Ten-year compound annual growth rate in basic eps (cont. ops).

Name: Basic EPS (Cont. Ops) CAGR (3y)
Description: Three-year compound annual growth rate in basic eps (cont. ops).

Name: Basic EPS (Cont. Ops) CAGR (5y)
Description: Five-year compound annual growth rate in basic eps (cont. ops).

Name: Basic EPS (Cont. Ops) CAGR (7y)
Description: Seven-year compound annual growth rate in basic eps (cont. ops).

Name: Basic EPS (Cont. Ops) Growth
Description: Period over prior period growth in basic eps (cont. ops).

Name: Basic EPS CAGR (10y)
Description: Ten-year compound annual growth rate in basic eps.

Name: Basic EPS CAGR (3y)
Description: Three-year compound annual growth rate in basic eps.

Name: Basic EPS CAGR (5y)
Description: Five-year compound annual growth rate in basic eps.

Name: Basic EPS CAGR (7y)
Description: Seven-year compound annual growth rate in basic eps.

Name: Basic EPS Growth
Description: Period over prior period growth in basic eps.

Name: Basic EPS Incl Extra Items
Description: Company's net earnings or losses from continuing operations adjusted for certain one-time items on a per basic share basis.

Name: Basic EPS, Adjusted
Description: This item represents Basic EPS excluding unusual items.

Name: Beginning Cash (CF)
Description: This item represents cash and cash equivalents as at the beginning of the period.

Name: Ben Graham Formula Upside
Description: The percentage increase (if positive) or decrease (if negative) an investor can expect over the current stock price based on the Ben Graham Formula Value. The Ben Graham Formula Value estimates a stock's intrinsic value based on a formula inspired by investor and professor, Benjamin Graham.

Name: Ben Graham Formula Value
Description: The Ben Graham Formula Value estimates a stock's intrinsic value based on a formula inspired by investor and professor, Benjamin Graham.

Name: Ben Graham Number
Description: A calculation inspired by Benjamin Graham often who is called the "father of value investing." The Graham Number estimates a stock's fundamental value by taking into account the company's earnings per share and book value per share.

Name: Ben Graham Number Upside
Description: The percentage increase (if positive) or decrease (if negative) an investor can expect over the current stock price based on the Ben Graham Number. The Ben Graham Number estimates a stock's intrinsic value based on a formula inspired by investor and professor, Benjamin Graham.

Name: Beneish M-Score
Description: A statistical score that uses financial ratios to identify whether a company has manipulated its earnings

Name: Beta (1 Year)
Description: A ratio that measures the risk or volatility of a company's share price in comparison to the market as a whole. Beta (1 Year) is calculated using one year of weekly returns.

Name: Beta (2 Year)
Description: A ratio that measures the risk or volatility of a company's share price in comparison to the market as a whole. Beta (2 Year) is calculated using two years of weekly returns.

Name: Beta (5 Year)
Description: A ratio that measures the risk or volatility of a company's share price in comparison to the market as a whole. A beta of 1.0 means that that the company rises and falls in direct relationship to the movement of the benchmark index. A beta that is less than 1 indicates a stock that is less volatile than the overall market and a beta greater than 1 indicates that the stock is more volatile.

Name: Book Value / Market Cap
Description: Compares a firm's common equity listed on the balance to the market value of equity.

Name: Book Value / Share
Description: The book value of common equity on a per basic share basis.

Name: Book Value per Share (Reported)
Description: If reported by the company, the book value of common equity on a per basic share basis. Use bv_share if you would like the value computed and normalized by us.

Name: Buildings
Description: This item represents the Assets of a durable nature in the form of Building held by the company, at their gross values, which are to be used in the production or sale of goods, sale of other goods or rendering of services rather than being held for sale.

Name: Business Divestitures
Description: This item represents cash inflows from disposition of a company, product line, operation, business or partial interest in a consolidated subsidiary.

Name: Buyback Yield
Description: A ratio that measures the difference between the amount of share repurchases and the amount of share issuances over the trailing twelve months divided by the company's market capitalization.

Name: Capital Expenditures
Description: The overall change in capital expenditures and sales of plant, property and equipment. This field is used if a company does not report separately sales and purchases of plant, property and equipment or is calculated as the sum of purchases and sales of PP&E

Name: Capital Expenditures Coverage
Description: The amount a company outlays for capital assets for each dollar of cash dollar it generates from those investments.

Name: Capital Expenditures Forecast
Description: Projected capital expenditures.

Name: Capital Expenditures Forecast Consensus Standard Deviation
Description: Standard deviation in forecasting capital expenditures.

Name: Capital Expenditures Forecast Count of Estimates
Description: The number of analysts publishing a capital expenditures forecast for the stock.

Name: Capital Expenditures Forecast High Consensus
Description: The highest capital expenditures forecast submitted by any analyst for the company.

Name: Capital Expenditures Forecast Low Consensus
Description: The lowest capital expenditures forecast submitted by any analyst for the company.

Name: Capital Expenditures Forecast Mean Consensus
Description: The mean or average capital expenditures forecast submitted by any analyst for the company.

Name: Capital Expenditures Forecast Median Consensus
Description: The median capital expenditures forecast submitted by any analyst for the company.

Name: Capital Expenditures Growth
Description: Period over prior period growth in capital expenditures.

Name: Capital Expenditures Growth Forecast
Description: Period over prior period growth in forecasted capital expenditures.

Name: Capital Expenditures Margin
Description: Capital expenditures expressed as percent of revenue.

Name: Capital Expenditures Margin Forecast
Description: Forecasted capital expenditures as a percent of forecasted revenue.

Name: Capital Leases
Description: The non-current portion of long term capital leases.

Name: Capitalized / Purchased Software
Description: Software and software development costs that are capitalized into an asset and amortized over time. This field is used if capitalized software is not included in plant, property and equipment line items.

Name: Cash / Total Capital
Description: A ratio that measures the level of the cash relative to the market value of total capital.

Name: Cash Acquisitions
Description: The amount of cash spent by the company to acquire companies in the given period.

Name: Cash Amount of Last Dividend
Description: Cash dividend amount on a per-share basis.

Name: Cash Amount of Last Dividend (Split Adj)
Description: Cash dividend amount on a per-share basis, adjusted for stock splits.

Name: Cash And Equivalents
Description: The amount of cash held by the company for the given period.

Name: Cash And Equivalents
Description: The amount of cash held by the company for the given period.

Name: Cash And ST Investments CAGR (10y)
Description: Ten-year compound annual growth rate in total cash and short-term investments.

Name: Cash And ST Investments CAGR (3y)
Description: Three-year compound annual growth rate in total cash and short-term investments.

Name: Cash And ST Investments CAGR (5y)
Description: Five-year compound annual growth rate in total cash and short-term investments.

Name: Cash And ST Investments CAGR (7y)
Description: Seven-year compound annual growth rate in total cash and short-term investments.

Name: Cash Conversion Cycle
Description: A metric that compares the amount of days it takes a company to sell inventory and collect receivables relative to the amount of days afforded to pay bills.

Name: Cash Deposits Interest Bearing
Description: This item represents cash deposits by customers in a bank, representing the depositors' right to an equivalent amount of money from the bank with interest.

Name: Cash Flow / Total Debt
Description: A ratio used in two ways - a) to measure cash flow coverage and b) the inverse ratio to estimate the length of time needed to pay off debts.

Name: Cash Flow to Current Liabilities
Description: A ratio that measures the amount of operating cash flow a firm generates on each dollar of current liabilities.

Name: Cash Flow to Liabilities
Description: A ratio that measures the amount of operating cash flow a firm generates on each dollar of total liabilities.

Name: Cash from Financing
Description: The net amount of cash transactions used in funding activities

Name: Cash from Investing
Description: The total change in cash resulting from a company's investments

Name: Cash from Operations
Description: A company's cash flows from operations.

Name: Cash Interest Paid
Description: The amount of interest expense paid by the company in cash for the given period.

Name: Cash Ratio
Description: A strict ratio used to assess a company's short-term liquidity.

Name: Cash Return On Invested Capital (CROIC)
Description: A ratio that measures the amount of free cash flow a firm generates on each dollar of capital invested (debt + equity).

Name: Change In Accounts Payable
Description: The increase or decrease in trade payables for the given period.

Name: Change In Accounts Receivable
Description: The increase or decrease in accounts receivable for the given period.

Name: Change In Income Taxes
Description: Changes in income tax accounts

Name: Change In Inventories
Description: The increase or decrease in a company's inventories for the period.

Name: Change in Net Working Capital
Description: Periodic change in Net Working Capital.

Name: Change in Other Net Operating Assets
Description: Changes in accounts payable and accrued liabilities

Name: Common Dividends Paid (CF)
Description: The cash outflow for dividends paid on a company's common stock

Name: Common Shares In Treasury
Description: This item represents the number of common shares repurchased or reacquired by the corporation (from market or directly from stockholders) at the end of a period

Name: Common Stock
Description: The value of net common equity ownership.

Name: Comprehensive Income and Other
Description: This item represents the residuary line items forming part of the shareholder's equity block which do not perfectly fit into any specific category or head.

Name: Comprehensive Income and Other (Bank)
Description: This item represents the sum total of changes in equity during a period from events relating to non-owner sources, the estimated amounts to be paid under contracts and all other items forming part of the Shareholder's Equity block which do not fit into any specific category or head.

Name: Consensus AFFO / Share, Actual
Description: Reported AFFO per share including any adjustments for unusual items proposed by management. This metric is useful for analyst forecast vs actual analysis since deciding which add backs are truly "unusual" is subjective.

Name: Consensus AFFO, Actual
Description: Reported AFFO including any adjustments for unusual items proposed by management. This metric is useful for analyst forecast vs actual analysis since deciding which add backs are truly "unusual" is subjective. Consider using "affo" slug instead for other analysis.

Name: Consensus Capital Expenditures, Actual
Description: Capital expenditures including any adjustments for unusual items proposed by management. This metric is useful for analyst forecast vs actual analysis. Consider using "capex" slug instead for other analysis.

Name: Consensus Dividends Per Share, Actual
Description: Dividends per share including any adjustments for unusual items proposed by management. This metric is useful for analyst forecast vs actual analysis. Consider using "div_share" slug instead for other analysis.

Name: Consensus EBIT, Actual
Description: Reported EBIT including any adjustments for unusual items proposed by management. This metric is useful for analyst forecast vs actual analysis since deciding which add backs are truly "unusual" is subjective. Consider using "ebit" slug instead for other analysis.

Name: Consensus EBITDA, Actual
Description: Reported EBITDA including any adjustments for unusual items proposed by management. This metric is useful for analyst forecast vs actual analysis since deciding which add backs are truly "unusual" is subjective. Consider using "ebitda" slug instead for other analysis.

Name: Consensus EPS, Actual
Description: Reported EPS including any adjustments for unusual items proposed by management. This metric is useful for analyst forecast vs actual analysis since deciding which add backs are truly "unusual" is subjective. Consider using "eps_diluted_cont" slug instead for other analysis.

Name: Consensus FFO / Share, Actual
Description: Reported FFO per share including any adjustments for unusual items proposed by management. This metric is useful for analyst forecast vs actual analysis since deciding which add backs are truly "unusual" is subjective.

Name: Consensus FFO, Actual
Description: Reported FFO including any adjustments for unusual items proposed by management. This metric is useful for analyst forecast vs actual analysis since deciding which add backs are truly "unusual" is subjective. Consider using "ffo" slug instead for other analysis.

Name: Consensus Net Income, Actual
Description: Reported net income including any adjustments for unusual items proposed by management. This metric is useful for analyst forecast vs actual analysis since deciding which add backs are truly "unusual" is subjective. Consider using "ni" slug instead for other analysis.

Name: Consensus Recommendation
Description: This item represents opinion expressed by the analysts on the stock performance over a short term period. Our data provider provides both the Broker Recommendations and Standardized Recommendations. Capital IQ will standardize all the individual recommendations across the brokers on a 1- 5 point scale. On this scale, 1 represents a Strong Buy, 3 a Hold and 5 a Sell.

Name: Consensus Revenue, Actual
Description: Reported revenue including any adjustments for unusual items proposed by management. This metric is useful for analyst forecast vs actual analysis since deciding which add backs are truly "unusual" is subjective. Consider using "total_rev" slug instead for other analysis.

Name: Construction in Progress
Description: This item represents that portion of gross assets (i.e. the capitalized amounts incurred on the construction of property) which are in the course of construction.

Name: Cost of Debt (After-tax)
Description: Our estimate of the after tax cost of debt for a company.

Name: Cost of Debt (Pre-tax)
Description: Our estimate of the pre tax cost of debt for a company.

Name: Cost of Equity
Description: Our estimate of the rate of return required by equity holders.

Name: Cost of Goods Sold Margin
Description: Cost Of Goods Sold (COGS) or Cost of Sales (COS) expressed as a percent of revenue.

Name: Cost of Goods Sold
Description: This expense item reflects production and sales costs.

Name: Cost of Revenue CAGR (10y)
Description: Ten-year compound annual growth rate in cost of revenue.

Name: Cost of Revenue CAGR (3y)
Description: Three-year compound annual growth rate in cost of revenue.

Name: Cost of Revenue CAGR (5y)
Description: Five-year compound annual growth rate in cost of revenue.

Name: Cost of Revenue CAGR (7y)
Description: Seven-year compound annual growth rate in cost of revenue.

Name: Cost of Revenue Growth
Description: Period over prior period growth in cost of revenue.

Name: Currency of Last Dividend
Description: Currency of the last dividend.

Name: Current Domestic Taxes
Description: This item represents the current amount of domestic taxes, payable by the company to its home country. For a US Company, taxes payable to U.S. government will be current domestic taxes. For a non-U.S. company, taxes payable to its own country government will be considered as current domestic taxes.

Name: Current Foreign Taxes
Description: This item represents the current amount of income taxes, payable by the company to countries other than its home country. For a U.S. company, taxes payable in another country will be foreign taxes. For a non-U.S. company, taxes payable to Government other than its home country will be foreign taxes.

Name: Current Income Taxes Payable
Description: This item represents accrued portion of Income taxes levied on the Corporate Income. If Income Taxes are combined with any other taxes or any other liabilities, where income taxes appear as first string and the company does not report the break up for the same, then the same will form part of this data item only.

Name: Current Portion of Capital Lease Obligations
Description: The portion of long term capital leases which is due in the upcoming year.

Name: Current Portion of LT Debt
Description: The portion of long term debt which is due in the upcoming year.

Name: Current Portion of LT Debt & Capital Leases
Description: The portion of long term debt and capital leases which is due in the upcoming year.

Name: Current Portion of Operating Lease Liabilities
Description: The portion of operating lease liabilities which is due in the upcoming year.

Name: Current Portion of Total Debt
Description: The sum of Short-term Borrowings, Current Portion of LT Debt and Capital Leases, Current due within the next year.

Name: Current Ratio
Description: A ratio that compares a company's current total assets to its current total liabilities.

Name: D&A Forecast
Description: Projected depreciation and amortization expense.

Name: Daily Close (Trading Days Only)
Description: The trading day's adjusted closing stock price. Only returns data for trading days.

Name: Daily High (Trading Days Only)
Description: The highest trading price a stock reached during a trading day. Only returns data for trading days.

Name: Daily Low (Trading Days Only)
Description: The lowest trading price a stock reached during a trading day. Only returns data for trading days.

Name: Daily Open (Trading Days Only)
Description: The trading day's adjusted opening stock price. Only returns data for trading days.

Name: Daily Stock Price High (Adjusted)
Description: The highest trade price over the trading day.

Name: Daily Stock Price Low (Adjusted)
Description: The lowest trade price over the trading day.

Name: Daily Stock Price Open (Adjusted)
Description: The opening trade price over the trading day.

Name: Damodaran's Industry Cost of Capital
Description: A general benchmark for the cost of capital in an industry based on research by Professor Damodaran at New York University, Stern.

Name: Damodaran's Industry Cost of Debt
Description: A general benchmark for the cost of debt in an industry based on research by Professor Damodaran at New York University, Stern.

Name: Damodaran's Industry Cost of Equity
Description: A general benchmark for the cost of equity in an industry based on research by Professor Damodaran at New York University, Stern.

Name: Days Inventory Outstanding
Description: A working capital efficiency ratio used to estimate the average number of days the firm holds inventory before selling it customers.

Name: Days Payables Outstanding
Description: A working capital efficiency ratio used to estimate the average number of days the firm has to pay its suppliers.

Name: Days Sales Outstanding
Description: A working capital efficiency ratio used to estimate the average number of days the firm takes to collect its receivables.

Name: Days To Next Earnings
Description: An estimate of the number of days until the next earnings report.

Name: Debt / Equity
Description: A ratio that measures the level of the debt relative to the book value of common equity.

Name: Debt / Tangible Equity
Description: A ratio that measures the level of the debt relative to the book value of tangible common equity.

Name: Debt Paydown Yield
Description: A ratio that measures the net change in long term debt over the trailing twelve months divided by the company's market capitalization.

Name: Deferred Charges Long-term
Description: Non-current costs that are deferred and amortized over time or prepaid and earned at a later date.

Name: Deferred Charges, Current
Description: A current asset arising from costs that have been paid where the benefits are deferred to a later date.

Name: Deferred Compensation
Description: An amount of stock set aside for purchase through employee compensation deferral plans.

Name: Deferred Domestic Taxes
Description: This item represents the deferred amount of domestic taxes, payable by the company to its home country. For a US Company, taxes deferred to the U.S. government will be deferred domestic taxes. For a non-U.S. company, taxes deferred to its own country government will be considered as deferred domestic taxes.

Name: Deferred Foreign Taxes
Description: This item represents the deferred amount of taxes, payable by the company to countries other than its home country. For a U.S. company, taxes deferred in another country will be deferred foreign taxes. For a non-U.S. company, taxes deferred to US Government will be deferred foreign taxes.

Name: Deferred Policy Acq. Costs
Description: This item represents the portion of policy acquisition costs deferred by the company. Expenses incurred on soliciting and acquiring new business is capitalized and amortized over the period of the policies. The amount charged to revenue each year is in the same proportion that annual premium received on a policy bears to the total premium receivable under that policy.

Name: Deferred Tax Assets Current
Description: An asset creating by a difference between accounting for income tax purposes and financial reporting purposes

Name: Deferred Tax Assets Long-Term (Bank)
Description: This item represents the deferred tax consequences of temporary differences (reversible differences between financial and tax reporting bases of assets) that will result into net tax deductions or carry forwards in future years. All temporary differences related to non-current assets, and all temporary differences reversible in more than one-year's time are included under this item.

Name: Deferred Tax Assets, Long-term
Description: A non-current asset created by a difference between accounting for income tax purposes and financial reporting purposes.

Name: Deferred Tax Liability Non-Current (Bank)
Description: This item represents an increase in taxes payable in future years that results from income that has already been earned for accounting purposes but not for tax purposes.

Name: Deferred Tax Liability, Current
Description: A liability created by a difference between accounting for income tax purposes and financial reporting purposes.

Name: Deferred Tax Liability, Long-term
Description: A liability created by a difference between accounting for income tax purposes and financial reporting purposes.

Name: Deposits at Interest in Securities (Bank)
Description: This item represents the Deposits made by the bank to earn interest but are not made part of cash and cash equivalents. This item includes interest-bearing deposits made part of Investments and excludes Restricted cash and interest-bearing deposits made part of cash and cash equivalents by the company.

Name: Depreciation & Amortization
Description: The sum of depreciation and amortization expenses.

Name: Depreciation & Amortization (Insurance)
Description: The sum of depreciation and amortization expenses for insurance companies.

Name: Depreciation & Amortization (IS)
Description: The sum of Depreciation and Amortization reported on the income statement for a given period.

Name: Depreciation & Amortization Growth
Description: Period over prior period growth in depreciation & amortization.

Name: Depreciation & Amortization Margin
Description: Depreciation and amortization as a percent of revenue.

Name: Depreciation & Amortization (CF)
Description:
This item represents non-cash periodical charge on account of wear and tear of fixed assets used in the business. This item also includes amortization of all intangible assets and goodwill.
Note: If the line reported in cash flow by the company is "Depreciation, amortization and other non-cash charges", we exclude from this all amortizations towards deferred charges, stock based-compensation, impairment and other non-cash charges included in it.

Name: Derivative Trading Asset Securities
Description: This item represents both debt and equity securities, which reflect active and frequent buying and selling by the company with an intention to generate profits from short-term price movements. The main motto of investment is profit generation and not long-term holding or capital appreciation.

Name: Description
Description: A brief description of a company or stock.

Name: Diluted EPS (Cont. Ops)
Description: Company's net earnings or losses from continuing operations on a per diluted share basis.

Name: Diluted EPS (Cont. Ops) CAGR (10y)
Description: Ten-year compound annual growth rate in diluted eps (cont. ops).

Name: Diluted EPS (Cont. Ops) CAGR (3y)
Description: Three-year compound annual growth rate in dil. eps (cont. ops).

Name: Diluted EPS (Cont. Ops) CAGR (5y)
Description: Five-year compound annual growth rate in dil. eps (cont. ops).

Name: Diluted EPS (Cont. Ops) CAGR (7y)
Description: Seven-year compound annual growth rate in dil. eps (cont. ops).

Name: Diluted EPS (Cont. Ops) Growth
Description: Period over prior period growth in dil. eps (cont. ops).

Name: Diluted EPS CAGR (10y)
Description: Ten-year compound annual growth rate in diluted eps.

Name: Diluted EPS CAGR (3y)
Description: Three-year compound annual growth rate in dil. eps.

Name: Diluted EPS CAGR (5y)
Description: Five-year compound annual growth rate in dil. eps.

Name: Diluted EPS CAGR (7y)
Description: Seven-year compound annual growth rate in dil. eps.

Name: Diluted EPS Growth
Description: Period over prior period growth in dil. eps.

Name: Diluted EPS Incl Extra Items
Description: Company's net earnings or losses from continuing operations adjusted for certain one-time items on a per diluted share basis.

Name: Diluted EPS, Adjusted
Description: This item represents Diluted EPS excluding unusual items.

Name: Dividend Adjustment Factor
Description: This item allows you to adjust the stock price return over a period of time to include income from dividends paid by the company.

Name: Dividend CAGR (10y)
Description: Ten-year compound annual growth rate in dividend.

Name: Dividend CAGR (3y)
Description: Three-year compound annual growth rate in dividend per share.

Name: Dividend CAGR (5y)
Description: Five-year compound annual growth rate in dividend per share.

Name: Dividend CAGR (7y)
Description: Seven-year compound annual growth rate in dividend per share.

Name: Dividend Coverage Ratio
Description: A ratio that measures the cash cushion available to management to maintain the firm's dividend to common shareholders.

Name: Dividend Currency
Description: The currency in which a company declares a dividend.

Name: Dividend Frequency
Description: The frequency with which a company typically pays dividends.

Name: Dividend Growth
Description: The growth rate in dividends per share.

Name: Dividend Per Share
Description: The dividend paid to shareholders for each share of stock. For quarterly dividend payers, it's common practice to multiply the most recent dividend by 4 to calculate dividend per share. Special dividends are not included in the calculation unless the company pays the dividend consistently in more than 1 period.

Name: Dividend Yield
Description: Measures the cash returned to shareholders by a firm as a percentage of the price they pay for each share of stock.

Name: Dividends Per Share Forecast
Description: Projected dividends per share.

Name: Dividends Per Share Forecast Consensus Standard Deviation
Description: Standard deviation in forecasted Dividends Per Share.

Name: Dividends Per Share Forecast Count of Estimates
Description: The number of analysts publishing a Dividends Per Share Forecast for the stock.

Name: Dividends Per Share Forecast High Consensus
Description: The highest Dividends Per Share Forecast submitted by any analyst for the company.

Name: Dividends Per Share Forecast Low Consensus
Description: The lowest Dividends Per Share Forecast submitted by any analyst for the company.

Name: Dividends Per Share Forecast Mean Consensus
Description: The mean or average Dividends Per Share Forecast submitted by any analyst for the company.

Name: Dividends Per Share Forecast Median Consensus
Description: The median Dividends Per Share Forecast submitted by any analyst for the company.

Name: Downside (Analyst Target)
Description: The percentage decrease (if positive) or increase (if negative) that professional analysts expect over the current stock price.

Name: Earnings of Discontinued Ops.
Description: This item represents the total of income (loss), net of tax, from operations of the discontinued division. It includes the gain (loss) on the sale of the division.

Name: Earnings Yield
Description: The inverse of the price-to-earnings ratio for the latest twelve months.

Name: EBIT
Description: Income before interest and taxes adjusted for certain one-time items.

Name: EBIT CAGR (10y)
Description: Ten-year compound annual growth rate in ebit.

Name: EBIT CAGR (3y)
Description: Three-year compound annual growth rate in EBIT.

Name: EBIT CAGR (5y)
Description: Five-year compound annual growth rate in EBIT.

Name: EBIT CAGR (7y)
Description: Seven-year compound annual growth rate in EBIT.

Name: EBIT Forecast
Description: Forecasted earnings before interest and taxes (EBIT).

Name: EBIT Forecast CAGR (10y)
Description: Ten year compound annual growth rate in forecasted earnings before interest and taxes (EBIT).

Name: EBIT Forecast CAGR (5y)
Description: Five year compound annual growth rate in forecasted earnings before interest and taxes (EBIT).

Name: EBIT Forecast Consensus Standard Deviation
Description: Standard deviation in forecasted EBIT.

Name: EBIT Forecast Count of Estimates
Description: The number of analysts publishing a EBIT Forecast for the stock.

Name: EBIT Forecast High Consensus
Description: The highest EBIT Forecast submitted by any analyst for the company.

Name: EBIT Forecast Low Consensus
Description: The lowest EBIT Forecast submitted by any analyst for the company.

Name: EBIT Forecast Mean Consensus
Description: The mean or average EBIT Forecast submitted by any analyst for the company.

Name: EBIT Forecast Median Consensus
Description: The median EBIT Forecast submitted by any analyst for the company.

Name: EBIT Growth
Description: Period over prior period growth in EBIT.

Name: EBIT Growth Forecast
Description: Period over prior period growth in forecasted earnings before interest and taxes (EBIT).

Name: EBIT Margin
Description: Earnings before interest and taxes (EBIT) expressed as a percent of revenue.

Name: EBIT Margin CAGR (10y)
Description: Ten-year compound annual growth rate in EBIT margin.

Name: EBIT Margin CAGR (3y)
Description: Three-year compound annual growth rate in EBIT margin.

Name: EBIT Margin CAGR (5y)
Description: Five-year compound annual growth rate in EBIT margin.

Name: EBIT Margin CAGR (7y)
Description: Seven-year compound annual growth rate in EBIT margin.

Name: EBIT Margin Forecast
Description: Forecasted earnings before interest and taxes (EBIT) as a percent of forecasted revenue.

Name: EBITA
Description: Earnings before interest, taxes and amortization (EBITA) adjusted for certain one-time items.

Name: EBITA Margin
Description: Earnings before interest, taxes and amortization (EBITA) expressed as a percent of revenue.

Name: EBITDA
Description: Income before interest, taxes, depreciation and amortization adjusted for certain one-time items.

Name: EBITDA - 3Yr Avg CapEx
Description: Earnings before interest, taxes, depreciation and amortization (EBITDA) minus three year average capital expenditures.

Name: EBITDA - CAPEX
Description: Earnings before interest, taxes, depreciation and amortization (EBITDA) minus capital expenditures.

Name: EBITDA CAGR (10y)
Description: Ten-year compound annual growth rate in ebitda.

Name: EBITDA CAGR (3y)
Description: Three-year compound annual growth rate in EBITDA.

Name: EBITDA CAGR (5y)
Description: Five-year compound annual growth rate in EBITDA.

Name: EBITDA CAGR (7y)
Description: Seven-year compound annual growth rate in EBITDA.

Name: EBITDA Forecast
Description: Forecasted earnings before interest, taxes, depreciation and amortization (EBITDA).

Name: EBITDA Forecast CAGR (10y)
Description: Ten year compound annual growth rate in forecasted earnings before interest, taxes, depreciation and amortization (EBITDA).

Name: EBITDA Forecast CAGR (5y)
Description: Five year compound annual growth rate in forecasted earnings before interest, taxes, depreciation and amortization (EBITDA).

Name: EBITDA Forecast Consensus Standard Deviation
Description: Standard deviation in forecasted EBITDA.

Name: EBITDA Forecast Count of Estimates
Description: The number of analysts publishing a EBITDA Forecast for the stock.

Name: EBITDA Forecast High Consensus
Description: The highest EBITDA Forecast submitted by any analyst for the company.

Name: EBITDA Forecast Low Consensus
Description: The lowest EBITDA Forecast submitted by any analyst for the company.

Name: EBITDA Forecast Mean Consensus
Description: The mean or average EBITDA Forecast submitted by any analyst for the company.

Name: EBITDA Forecast Median Consensus
Description: The median EBITDA Forecast submitted by any analyst for the company.

Name: EBITDA Growth
Description: Period over prior period growth in EBITDA.

Name: EBITDA Growth Forecast
Description: Period over prior period growth in forecasted earnings before interest, taxes, depreciation and amortization (EBITDA).

Name: EBITDA Interest Coverage Ratio
Description: A ratio used to assess a firm's ability to pay interest expenses based on EBITDA.

Name: EBITDA less CapEx Interest Coverage Ratio
Description: A ratio used to assess a firm's ability to pay interest expenses based on EBITDA less Capital Expenditures.

Name: EBITDA Margin
Description: Earnings before interest, taxes, depreciation and amortization (EBITDA) expressed as a percent of revenue.

Name: EBITDA Margin CAGR (10y)
Description: Ten-year compound annual growth rate in EBITDA margin.

Name: EBITDA Margin CAGR (3y)
Description: Three-year compound annual growth rate in EBITDA margin.

Name: EBITDA Margin CAGR (5y)
Description: Five-year compound annual growth rate in EBITDA margin.

Name: EBITDA Margin CAGR (7y)
Description: Seven-year compound annual growth rate in EBITDA margin.

Name: EBITDA Margin Forecast
Description: Forecasted earnings before interest, taxes, depreciation and amortization (EBITDA) as a percent of forecasted revenue.

Name: EBITDA minus 3Yr Avg CapEx Margin
Description: Earnings before interest, taxes, depreciation and amortization (EBITDA) minus three year average capital expenditures expressed as a percent of revenue.

Name: EBITDA minus CAPEX Margin
Description: Earnings before interest, taxes, depreciation and amortization (EBITDA) minus capital expenditures expressed as a percent of revenue.

Name: EBITDAR
Description: Earnings before interest, taxes, depreciation, amortization, and rent costs (EBITDAR) adjusted for certain one-time items.

Name: EBT Excl. Unusual Items
Description: This item represents EBT Before Non Recurring Items and is arrived at after adjusting, the following, to Operating Profit (OPIN): 1. Interest Expense, Total and 2. Total Non Operating Income/(Expenses) (NOIET).

Name: EBT, Incl. Unusual Items
Description: Company's earnings or loss before taxes on income have been accounted for.

Name: EBT, Incl. Unusual Items CAGR (10y)
Description: Ten-year compound annual growth rate in ebt, incl. unusual items.

Name: EBT, Incl. Unusual Items CAGR (3y)
Description: Three-year compound annual growth rate in pre-tax income.

Name: EBT, Incl. Unusual Items CAGR (5y)
Description: Five-year compound annual growth rate in pre-tax income.

Name: EBT, Incl. Unusual Items CAGR (7y)
Description: Seven-year compound annual growth rate in pre-tax income.

Name: EBT, Incl. Unusual Items Growth
Description: Period over prior period growth in pre-tax income.

Name: Effective Interest Rate
Description: In the context of a firm's debts, effective interest rate is calculated as Interest Expense divided by Total Debt.

Name: Effective Tax Rate
Description: A ratio that measures the GAAP tax rate applicable to the earnings after all expenses have been deducted by the business.

Name: Ending Cash (CF)
Description: This item represents cash and cash equivalents as at the end of the period.

Name: Enterprise Value (EV)
Description: Enterprise Value (EV), also referred to as Business Enterprise Value (BEV), reflects the market value of the entire business. Unlikely Total Enterprise Value (TEV), EV excludes value related to the non-operating assets of the business.

Name: Entity Type
Description: The type of entity (company, etf, closed-end fund, etc.)

Name: EPS Forecast
Description: Forecasted earnings per share (EPS).

Name: EPS Forecast Consensus Standard Deviation
Description: Standard deviation in forecasted EPS.

Name: EPS Forecast Count of Estimates
Description: The number of analysts publishing a EPS Forecast for the stock.

Name: EPS Forecast High Consensus
Description: The highest EPS Forecast submitted by any analyst for the company.

Name: EPS Forecast Low Consensus
Description: The lowest EPS Forecast submitted by any analyst for the company.

Name: EPS Forecast Mean Consensus
Description: The mean or average EPS Forecast submitted by any analyst for the company.

Name: EPS Forecast Median Consensus
Description: The median EPS Forecast submitted by any analyst for the company.

Name: EPS Growth Forecast
Description: Period over prior period growth in forecasted earnings per share (EPS).

Name: EPS, Adjusted w/ Current Shares Out
Description: This item represents Diluted EPS excluding unusual items. Note, this calculation uses the latest current shares outstanding.

Name: EPV Adjusted Earnings
Description: A measure of free cash flow made famous by Columbia University Professor Bruce Greenwald. Adjusted earnings is calculated by estimating a "sustainable" level of revenues and profits based on historical trends.

Name: Equity Method Investments
Description: This item represents all those non-current investments held by the company, which are accounted for by the equity method of accounting.

Name: EV / EBIT
Description: Measures the dollars in Enterprise Value for each dollar of EBIT over the last twelve months.

Name: EV / EBITDA
Description: Measures the dollars in Enterprise Value for each dollar of EBITDA over the last twelve months.

Name: EV / Free Cash Flow
Description: Measures the dollars in Enterprise Value for each dollar of free cash flow over the last twelve months.

Name: EV / Fwd EBIT
Description: Measures the dollars in Enterprise Value for each dollar of EBIT projected to be earned over the next twelve months.

Name: EV / Fwd EBITDA
Description: Measures the dollars in Enterprise Value for each dollar of EBITDA projected to be earned over the next twelve months.

Name: EV / Fwd EBITDA - CAPEX
Description: Measures the dollars in Enterprise Value for each dollar of EBITDA minus Capital Expenditures projected to be earned over the next twelve months.

Name: EV / Fwd Revenue
Description: Measures the dollars in Enterprise Value for each dollar of revenue projected to be earned over the next twelve months.

Name: EV / Invested Capital
Description: Measures the dollars in Enterprise Value for each dollar of Invested Capital (Equity + Debt) over the last twelve months.

Name: EV / LTM EBITDA - CAPEX
Description: Measures the dollars in Enterprise Value for each dollar of EBITDA minus Capital Expenditures over the last twelve months.

Name: EV / Revenue
Description: Measures the dollars in Enterprise Value for each dollar of revenue over the last twelve months.

Name: Ex-Date of Last Dividend
Description: Ex-dividend date is usually two business days before the dividend record date. Shares purchased on or after the ex-dividend date are not eligible to receive the next dividend payment.

Name: Extraordinary Item & Account Change
Description: This item represents the extraordinary income (loss) and also includes the cumulative effect of change in the accounting policies of the company, reported by the company after net income from continuing and discontinued operations.

Name: Extraordinary Items
Description: This item represents an unusual one-time gain or loss on the income statement. As per US GAAP, companies require that Extraordinary Items must be separately disclosed in the income statement, net of any related tax effects, after discontinued operations and before the cumulative effect of changes in accounting principle. Extraordinary Items as per U.S. GAAP has a different meaning than that of the dictionary meaning. Generally 'Gain/Loss on early retirement/extinguishment of debt' are reported as Extraordinary Items by U.S. companies.

Name: Fair Value (Analyst Target)
Description: The average of analyst price targets for a stock. Price targets represent what analysts believe a stock will be worth within the next 12 to 18 months.

Name: Fair Value
Description: Represents the fair value estimated using our valuation models.

Name: Fair Value Confidence
Description: Represents the uncertainty rating we have assigned to our Fair Value estimate.

Name: Fair Value Downside
Description: The percentage decrease (if positive) or increase (if negative) that our models estimate over the current stock price.

Name: Fair Value Uncertainty
Description: Represents the uncertainty rating we have assigned to our Fair Value estimate.

Name: Fair Value Upside
Description: The percentage increase (if positive) or decrease (if negative) that our models estimate over the current stock price.

Name: FCF / OCF
Description: A ratio that measures the amount of free cash flows (FCF) for each dollar of operating cash flows (OCF).

Name: FFO / Share Forecast Consensus Standard Deviation
Description: Standard deviation in forecasted FFO / Share.

Name: FFO / Share Forecast Count of Estimates
Description: The number of analysts publishing a FFO / Share Forecast for the stock.

Name: FFO / Share Forecast High Consensus
Description: The highest FFO / Share Forecast submitted by any analyst for the company.

Name: FFO / Share Forecast Low Consensus
Description: The lowest FFO / Share Forecast submitted by any analyst for the company.

Name: FFO / Share Forecast Mean Consensus
Description: The mean or average FFO / Share Forecast submitted by any analyst for the company.

Name: FFO / Share Forecast Median Consensus
Description: The median FFO / Share Forecast submitted by any analyst for the company.

Name: FFO Forecast
Description: Forecasted funds from operations (FFO).

Name: FFO Forecast CAGR (10y)
Description: Ten year compound annual growth rate in forecasted funds from operations.

Name: FFO Forecast CAGR (5y)
Description: Five year compound annual growth rate in forecasted funds from operations.

Name: FFO Forecast Consensus Standard Deviation
Description: Standard deviation in forecasted FFO.

Name: FFO Forecast Count of Estimates
Description: The number of analysts publishing a FFO Forecast for the stock.

Name: FFO Forecast High Consensus
Description: The highest FFO Forecast submitted by any analyst for the company.

Name: FFO Forecast Low Consensus
Description: The lowest FFO Forecast submitted by any analyst for the company.

Name: FFO Forecast Mean Consensus
Description: The mean or average FFO Forecast submitted by any analyst for the company.

Name: FFO Forecast Median Consensus
Description: The median FFO Forecast submitted by any analyst for the company.

Name: FFO Growth Forecast
Description: Period over prior period growth in forecasted net working capital (NWC).

Name: FFO Margin Forecast
Description: Forecasted funds from operations as a percent of forecasted revenue.

Name: Finance Division Debt, Current
Description: This item represents those amounts pertaining to the finance division of an Industrial template company, which are in the nature of debt and are currently payable within one year or within the operating cycle of the business, usually with interest.

Name: Finance Division Debt, Long-Term
Description: This item represents those amounts pertaining to the finance division of an Industrial template company, which are to be repaid in full, usually with interest, that are not currently payable within one year or within the operating cycle of the business.

Name: Financial Leverage
Description: A ratio that measures the dollars in total assets for each dollar of common equity.

Name: First Trade Date (Trading Item)
Description: The date the subject security started trading on an exchange

Name: Fixed Asset Turnover
Description: An efficiency ratio that is calculated by dividing revenue by average fixed assets.

Name: Float Shares / Outstanding
Description: The percentage of outstanding shares that are available for trading.

Name: Forecast Currency
Description: The currency in which a company's analysts forecast data for the company.

Name: Foreign Exchange Rate
Description: The foreign exchange rate between two currencies.

Name: Foreign Exchange Rate Adjustments
Description: The change in cash arising from fluctuating foreign exchange rates.

Name: Free Cash Flow Payout Ratio
Description: A ratio that is calculated as total dividends paid divided by levered free cash flow.

Name: Free Cash Flow Yield
Description: Measures amount of free cash flow for each dollar of equity (market capitalization).

Name: Full Ticker
Description: The fully qualified ticker in EXCHANGE:SYMBOL format

Name: Full Time Employees
Description: The number of full time employees that the company employs. This metric is only available when the data is reported in company filings.

Name: Fund Asset Class
Description: The asset class a fund is primarily focused on.

Name: Fund Asset Focus
Description: The primary focus within a category the fund is targeting.

Name: Fund Benchmark Index
Description: The index the fund benchmarks performance against.

Name: Fund Brand
Description: The name of the public brand of the issuer.

Name: Fund Category
Description: The category within an asset class the fund is targeting.

Name: Fund Economic Focus
Description: The economic region a fund is primarily focused on.

Name: Fund Expense Ratio
Description: Expense ratio of fund or security

Name: Fund Geography
Description: The geography a fund is targeting.

Name: Fund Is Actively Managed
Description: Is the fund actively managed?

Name: Fund Is ETN
Description: Is the fund an Exchange Traded Note (ETN)?

Name: Fund Is Inverse
Description: Is the fund's performance inverse of the target asset class or category?

Name: Fund Is Leveraged
Description: Does the fund use additional leverage?

Name: Fund Issuer
Description: Issuer of fund.

Name: Fund Launch Date
Description: Date of launch for a fund.

Name: Fund Niche
Description: The primary niche the fund is targeting.

Name: Funds From Operations
Description: A measure typically used to evaluate REITs calculated by adding depreciation and amortization to earnings, subtracting any gains on sales.

Name: Funds From Operations Growth
Description: Period over prior period growth in funds from operations (FFO).

Name: Funds From Operations Margin
Description: Adjusted funds from operations (AFFO) expressed as a percent of revenue.

Name: Fwd Earnings Yield
Description: The inverse of the forward price-to-earnings ratio.

Name: Fwd EBIT Yield
Description: Compares the earnings before interest and taxes (EBIT) to the market's valuation of the entire business, including debt and equity.

Name: Gain (Loss) On Sale Of Assets
Description:
This item represents any gain or loss on sale/disposition of tangible and
intangible fixed assets, subsidiaries, division, segment, product line,
business, operations etc and is of non-recurring in nature.

Name: Gain (Loss) on Sale of Assets (REIT)
Description: This item represents any gain or loss on sale of fixed or intangible assets and is of non-recurring nature.

Name: Gain (Loss) on Sale of Assets (Bank Rev)
Gain (Loss) On Sale Of Invest.
Description:
This item represents any realized or unrealized gain (loss) on sale of
marketable securities or investments in joint ventures, affiliates,
partnerships, unconsolidated subsidiaries.

Name: Gain on Sale of Invest. & Secur. (Bank Rev)
General & Admin Expenses
Description: This item represents the general and administrative costs incurred by the company.

Name: Goodwill
Description: This item represents the excess of purchase price paid over the fair market value of net assets acquired, net of any write downs for impairment in value. Goodwill is now no longer amortized over an estimated useful life as was being done earlier (prior to SFAS 142). Instead the balance of goodwill has to be assessed at every reporting period and a write down for impairment has to be recognized when determined. The assessment for impairment is done by applying a fair value based test.

Name: Goodwill & Intangibles
Description: The sum of all intangible asset fields

Name: Gross Profit
Description: Revenues from operations less the associated costs.

Name: Gross Profit CAGR (10y)
Description: Ten-year compound annual growth rate in gross profit.

Name: Gross Profit CAGR (3y)
Description: Three-year compound annual growth rate in gross profit.

Name: Gross Profit CAGR (5y)
Description: Five-year compound annual growth rate in gross profit.

Name: Gross Profit CAGR (7y)
Description: Seven-year compound annual growth rate in gross profit.

Name: Gross Profit Growth
Description: Period over prior period growth in gross profit.

Name: Gross Profit Margin
Description: Gross profit expressed as a percent of revenue.

Name: Gross Profit Margin CAGR (10y)
Description: Ten-year compound annual growth rate in gross profit margin.

Name: Gross Profit Margin CAGR (3y)
Description: Three-year compound annual growth rate in gross profit margin.

Name: Gross Profit Margin CAGR (5y)
Description: Five-year compound annual growth rate in gross profit margin.

Name: Gross Profit Margin CAGR (7y)
Description: Seven-year compound annual growth rate in gross profit margin.

Name: Gross Property Plant And Equipment
Description: The sum of all gross property, plant & equipment fields. Where companies do not report a breakdown of plant, property, & equipment, the value is entered in this field alone.

Name: Impairment of Goodwill
Description: A charge off occurring when the carrying value of goodwill is less than its market value. When this happens the goodwill is written off so that its carrying value matches up with its market value.

Name: Implied Shares Outstanding
Description: Implied shares outstanding of company's equity shares including partnership interests.

Name: In Process R&D Expenses
Description: This item represents when a company acquired other companys assets and liabilities along with its in process R&D and if that In process R&D is of no use to Acquired Company, it will be written off.

Name: Income on Real Estate Property (Bank Rev)
Income Tax Expense
Description: The total amount of income tax expense for the given period.

Name: Income Tax Expense CAGR (10y)
Description: Ten-year compound annual growth rate in income tax expense.

Name: Income Tax Expense CAGR (3y)
Description: Three-year compound annual growth rate in provision for taxes.

Name: Income Tax Expense CAGR (5y)
Description: Five-year compound annual growth rate in provision for taxes.

Name: Income Tax Expense CAGR (7y)
Description: Seven-year compound annual growth rate in provision for taxes.

Name: Income Tax Expense Margin
Description: A ratio that measures the GAAP taxes applicable to the earnings after all expenses have been deducted by the business as a percent of revenue.

Name: Income Tax Growth
Description: Period over prior period growth in provision for taxes.

Name: Index Membership
Description: The indices that use a stock as part of its price calculation.

Name: Industry (GICS)
Description: The industry in which a company operates.

Name: Industry Group (GICS)
Description: The industry group in which a company operates.

Name: Insurance Settlements
Description: This item represents Proceeds from insurance claims received by a company from its insurance carrier.

Name: Interest And Invest. Income (Rev)
Description: Interest income from loans made, or income related to investments made, as a normal part of daily operations.

Name: Interest And Investment Income
Description: This item represents the interest and investment income derived from investments made out of surplus funds.

Name: Interest Capitalized
Description: Interest expense that has been capitalized as an asset and is amortized over a defined period.

Name: Interest Coverage Ratio
Description: A ratio used to assess a firm's ability to pay interest expenses based on operating profits (EBIT).

Name: Interest Expense Margin
Description: Interest expense expressed as a percent of revenue.

Name: Interest Expense
Description: The costs incurred from non-operating borrowings for the given period.

Name: Interest Expense (Bank)
Description: Interest paid on loans that are deemed to be necessary as a normal part of daily operations.

Name: Interest Expense CAGR (10y)
Description: Ten-year compound annual growth rate in interest expense, total.

Name: Interest Expense CAGR (3y)
Description: Three-year compound annual growth rate in interest expense.

Name: Interest Expense CAGR (5y)
Description: Five-year compound annual growth rate in interest expense.

Name: Interest Expense CAGR (7y)
Description: Seven-year compound annual growth rate in interest expense.

Name: Interest Expense Growth
Description: Period over prior period growth in interest expense.

Name: Interest on Long-Term Debt
Description: This item represents gross amount of interest on long-term debt.

Name: Inventory
Description: The total value of inventories in all stages of completion.

Name: Inventory Long-Term
Description: This item represents the non-current inventories of the motion picture film industry comprising of certain capitalized costs incurred for the acquisition and production of entertainment properties.

Name: Inventory Method
Description: The inventory record keeping method used by the company (FIFO / LIFO).

Name: Inventory Turnover
Description: A ratio that measures the number for times a company's inventory is sold and replaced over the year.

Name: Investment In Equity and Pref. Securities
Invest. In Marketable & Equity Securities
Description: This item represents cash flows towards purchase or sale of all investments made by the company whether such investments are short-term or long-term, accounted under equity or cost method, available-for-sale or held-to-maturity.

Name: Issuance of Common Stock
Description: The amount of cash received by the company from issuing company stock in the given period.

Name: Land
Description: This item represents the Assets of a durable nature in the form of Land held by the company, at their gross values, which are to be used in the production or sale of goods, sale of other goods or rendering of services rather than being held for sale.

Name: Last Period End Date
Description: The most recent reporting period end date

Name: Last Reported Fiscal Period Key
Description: The most recent reporting period fiscal period in our period format. Latest final key Example: FY${fiscal_year}.Q${fiscal_qtr}

Name: Last Reported Fiscal Quarter
Description: The most recent reporting period fiscal quarter

Name: Last Reported Fiscal Year
Description: The most recent reporting period fiscal year

Name: Legal Settlements
Description: Income or expenses associated with legal matters including settlements, patents and provisions for future legal costs.

Name: Levered Free Cash Flow
Description: The sum of cash from operations and capital expenditures.

Name: Levered Free Cash Flow Growth
Description: Period over prior period growth in levered free cash flow.

Name: Levered Free Cash Flow Margin
Description: Levered free cash flow expressed as a percent of revenue.

Name: Loans & Advances to Clients
Description: Advances and deposits that offer benefits in the future.

Name: Long Term Earnings Growth Rate
Description: Forecasted long term earnings growth rate.

Name: Long Term Growth % Consensus Standard Deviation
Description: Standard deviation in forecasted Long Term Growth %.

Name: Long Term Growth % Count of Estimates
Description: The number of analysts publishing a Long Term Growth % for the stock.

Name: Long Term Growth % High Consensus
Description: The highest Long Term Growth % submitted by any analyst for the company.

Name: Long Term Growth % Low Consensus
Description: The lowest Long Term Growth % submitted by any analyst for the company.

Name: Long Term Growth % Mean Consensus
Description: The mean or average Long Term Growth % submitted by any analyst for the company.

Name: Long Term Growth % Median Consensus
Description: The median Long Term Growth % submitted by any analyst for the company.

Name: Long-Term Accounts Receivables
Description: Notes, loans, accounts and other receivables expected in more than one year.

Name: Long-term Debt
Description: The sum of all long term debt fields.

Name: Long-Term Debt Issued
Description: This item represents cash inflow on issuance of any debt that is long-term in nature.

Name: Long-Term Debt Repaid
Description: This item represents cash outflows towards repayment of any debt that is long-term in nature.

Name: Long-term Investments
Description: The aggregate value of debt and or equity investments with maturities or benefits lasting more than one year.

Name: Loss (Income) On Equity Investments
Description: Net losses or gains arising from the sale of equity investments, securities and/or derivative assets.

Name: LTM EBIT Yield
Description: Compares the earnings before interest and taxes (EBIT) to the market's valuation of the entire business, including debt and equity.

Name: Machinery
Description: This item represents the Assets of a durable nature held by the company, at their gross values, which are to be used in the production or sale of goods, sale of other goods or rendering of services rather than being held for sale. This is the residual item consisting of all the types of fixed assets not classifiable as either Land or Building.

Name: Marginal Tax Rate
Description: Marginal tax rate used for financial modeling.

Name: Market Cap
Description: Measures a public company's total equity value as implied by the stock's last observed trading price.

Name: Market Cap (Implied)
Description: The implied market capitalization of the company including limited partner shares.

Name: Market Cap / Fwd Revenue
Description: Indicates the multiple of forward revenue that stock investors are willing to pay for one share of the firm.

Name: Market Cap / LTM Revenue
Description: Indicates the multiple of revenue that stock investors are willing to pay for one share of the firm.

Name: Merger & Related Restructuring Charges
Description: Expenses related to corporate actions including mergers, acquisitions and spin-offs.

Name: Merger & Restructuring Charges
