Description: This item represents the sum of one-time Merger and Restructuring charges incurred by the company.

Name: Minority Interest in Earnings
Description: The reporting company's share of ownership in another company by including income or loss of the company as a portion of Net Income.

Name: Minority Interest in Earnings CAGR (10y)
Description: Ten-year compound annual growth rate in minority interest in earnings.

Name: Minority Interest in Earnings CAGR (3y)
Description: Three-year compound annual growth rate in minority interest in earnings.

Name: Minority Interest in Earnings CAGR (5y)
Description: Five-year compound annual growth rate in minority interest in earnings.

Name: Minority Interest in Earnings CAGR (7y)
Description: Seven-year compound annual growth rate in minority interest in earnings.

Name: Minority Interest in Earnings Growth
Description: Period over prior period growth in minority interest in earnings.

Name: Minority Interest in Earnings Margin
Description: Minority Interest in Earnings expressed as a percent of revenue.

Name: Name
Description: The name of the company of stock.

Name: NAV / Share
Description: Net Asset Value per share as estimated by analysts.

Name: NAV / Share Forecast Consensus Standard Deviation
Description: The median NAV / share forecast submitted by any analyst for the company.

Name: NAV / Share Forecast Count of Estimates
Description: Standard deviation in forecasted NAV / share.

Name: NAV / Share Forecast High Consensus
Description: The number of analysts publishing a NAV / share forecast for the stock.

Name: NAV / Share Forecast Low Consensus
Description: The highest NAV / share forecast submitted by any analyst for the company.

Name: NAV / Share Forecast Mean Consensus
Description: The lowest NAV / share forecast submitted by any analyst for the company.

Name: NAV / Share Forecast Median Consensus
Description: The mean or average NAV / share forecast submitted by any analyst for the company.

Name: NAV Forecast Consensus Standard Deviation
Description: The median Net Asset Value (NAV) forecast submitted by any analyst for the company.

Name: NAV Forecast Count of Estimates
Description: Standard deviation in forecasted Net Asset Value (NAV).

Name: NAV Forecast High Consensus
Description: The number of analysts publishing a Net Asset Value (NAV) forecast for the stock.

Name: NAV Forecast Low Consensus
Description: The highest Net Asset Value (NAV) forecast submitted by any analyst for the company.

Name: NAV Forecast Mean Consensus
Description: The lowest Net Asset Value (NAV) forecast submitted by any analyst for the company.

Name: NAV Forecast Median Consensus
Description: The mean or average Net Asset Value (NAV) forecast submitted by any analyst for the company.

Name: NCAV Per Share
Description: A calculation inspired by Benjamin Graham. Net Current Asset Value is calculated as current assets minus total liabilities. NCAV per share expresses this calculation on per share basis.

Name: Net (Increase) Dec. in Loans Originated/Sold - Investing
Description: This item represents change in loans given by the company in the course of its lending activity and proceeds from repayment of such loans.

Name: Net Asset Value
Description: Net Asset Value as estimated by analysts.

Name: Net Cash (Ben Graham)
Description: The sum of cash & short-term investments minus total liabilities.

Name: Net Cash from Discontinued Ops.
Description: This item represents operating cash flows relating to discontinued operations of the company.

Name: Net Change in Cash
Description: The total change in cash for the company over the given period.

Name: Net Current Asset Value (NCAV)
Description: A calculation inspired by Benjamin Graham. Net Current Asset Value is calculated as current assets minus total liabilities.

Name: Net Debt
Description: The sum of all long term debt fields minus cash and short-term investments.

Name: Net Debt / EBITDA
Description: A ratio that is calculated as net debt divided by EBITDA.

Name: Net Debt / Total Capital
Description: A ratio that measures the level of the net debt relative to the market value of total capital. Net debt is the sum of all long term debt fields minus cash and short-term investments.

Name: Net Debt Issued
Description: This item represents net cash flows from issuance or repayments of debt.

Name: Net Income (CF)
Description: This item represents the net earnings for the given period, as reported by the companies following indirect method of calculating cash flows from operations. In cases where the companies follow direct method of cash flow, this line item will be picked from income statement.

Name: Net Income Forecast
Description: Forecasted net income.

Name: Net Income Forecast CAGR (10y)
Description: Ten year compound annual growth rate in forecasted net income.

Name: Net Income Forecast CAGR (5y)
Description: Five year compound annual growth rate in forecasted net income.

Name: Net Income Forecast Consensus Standard Deviation
Description: Standard deviation in forecasted Net Income.

Name: Net Income Forecast Count of Estimates
Description: The number of analysts publishing a Net Income Forecast for the stock.

Name: Net Income Forecast High Consensus
Description: The highest Net Income Forecast submitted by any analyst for the company.

Name: Net Income Forecast Low Consensus
Description: The lowest Net Income Forecast submitted by any analyst for the company.

Name: Net Income Forecast Mean Consensus
Description: The mean or average Net Income Forecast submitted by any analyst for the company.

Name: Net Income Forecast Median Consensus
Description: The median Net Income Forecast submitted by any analyst for the company.

Name: Net Income Growth Forecast
Description: Period over prior period growth in forecasted net income.

Name: Net Income Margin Forecast
Description: Forecasted net income as a percent of forecasted revenue.

Name: Net Income to Common CAGR (10y)
Description: Ten-year compound annual growth rate in net income to common excluding extra items.

Name: Net Income to Common CAGR (3y)
Description: Three-year compound annual growth rate in net income to common excluding extra items.

Name: Net Income to Common CAGR (5y)
Description: Five-year compound annual growth rate in net income to common excluding extra items.

Name: Net Income to Common CAGR (7y)
Description: Seven-year compound annual growth rate in net income to common excluding extra items.

Name: Net Income to Common Excl Extra Items
Description: This item represents the net income or loss available to common stockholders and is arrived after adjusting preferred stock dividends and other adjustments to net income to stockholders (cont. ops).

Name: Net Income to Common Excl Extra Items Growth
Description: Period over prior period growth in net income to common excluding extra items.

Name: Net Income to Common Margin
Description: A ratio that measures the amount of profit from continuing operations that common shareholders earn on each dollar of revenue earned by the firm.

Name: Net Income to Common Incl Extra Items
Description: This item represents the Net Income (Loss) available to common stockholders and is arrived after adjusting preferred stock dividends and other adjustments to Net Income (Loss) Before Pref. Dividend (NIIN).

Name: Net Income to Common, Adjusted
Description: This item represents the net Income available to common shareholders of the company adjusted for unusual Items.

Name: Net Income to Company
Description: This item represents the net income available to all stakeholders of the company and is presented as total income or loss before discontinued operations, extraordinary items, preferred stock dividends and accounting change.

Name: Net Income to Company (Cont. Ops)
Description: This item represents the net income earned by the company from continuing operations. It is arrived at after adjusting, the following, to earnings before taxes (EBT) including non-recurring items: a) provision for income taxes (refund) b) minority interest, and c) U.S. GAAP adjustment.

Name: Net Income to Company (Cont. Ops) CAGR (10y)
Description: Ten-year compound annual growth rate in net income to company from continuing operations.

Name: Net Income to Company (Cont. Ops) CAGR (3y)
Description: Three-year compound annual growth rate in net income to company from continuing operations.

Name: Net Income to Company (Cont. Ops) CAGR (5y)
Description: Five-year compound annual growth rate in net income to company from continuing operations.

Name: Net Income to Company (Cont. Ops) CAGR (7y)
Description: Seven-year compound annual growth rate in net income to company from continuing operations.

Name: Net Income to Company (Cont. Ops) Growth
Description: Period over prior period growth in net income to company from continuing operations.

Name: Net Income to Company (Cont. Ops) Margin
Description: A ratio that measures the amount of profit from continuing operations that the company earns on each dollar of revenue.

Name: Net Income to Stockholders
Description: This item represents the net income or loss available to preferred and common stockholders and is arrived after adjusting net income to the company.

Name: Net Income to Stockholders CAGR (10y)
Description: Ten-year compound annual growth rate in net income to stockholders.

Name: Net Income to Stockholders CAGR (3y)
Description: Three-year compound annual growth rate in net income to stockholders.

Name: Net Income to Stockholders CAGR (5y)
Description: Five-year compound annual growth rate in net income to stockholders.

Name: Net Income to Stockholders CAGR (7y)
Description: Seven-year compound annual growth rate in net income to stockholders.

Name: Net Income to Shareholders Growth
Description: Period over prior period growth in net income to stockholders.

Name: Net Income to Stockholders Margin
Description: A ratio that measures the amount of profit that stockholders earn on each dollar of revenue earned by the firm.

Name: Net Income to Stockholders Margin CAGR (10y)
Description: Ten-year compound annual growth rate in net income to stockholders margin.

Name: Net Income to Stockholders Margin CAGR (3y)
Description: Three-year compound annual growth rate in net income to stockholders margin.

Name: Net Income to Stockholders Margin CAGR (5y)
Description: Five-year compound annual growth rate in net income to stockholders margin.

Name: Net Income to Stockholders Margin CAGR (7y)
Description: Seven-year compound annual growth rate in net income to stockholders margin.

Name: Net Income to Stockholders (Cont. Ops)
Description: This item represents the net income or loss available to preferred and common stockholders and is arrived after adjusting net income to the company from continuing operations.

Name: Net Income to Stockholders (Cont. Ops) CAGR (10y)
Description: Ten-year compound annual growth rate in net income to stockholders from continuing operations.

Name: Net Income to Stockholders (Cont. Ops) CAGR (3y)
Description: Three-year compound annual growth rate in net income to stockholders from continuing operations.

Name: Net Income to Stockholders (Cont. Ops) CAGR (5y)
Description: Five-year compound annual growth rate in net income to stockholders from continuing operations.

Name: Net Income to Stockholders (Cont. Ops) CAGR (7y)
Description: Seven-year compound annual growth rate in net income to stockholders from continuing operations.

Name: Net Income to Stockholders (Cont. Ops) Growth
Description: Period over prior period growth in net income to stockholders from continuing operations.

Name: Net Income to Stockholders (Cont. Ops) Margin
Description: A ratio that measures the amount of profit from continuing operations stockholders earn on each dollar of revenue earned by the firm.

Name: Net Interest Expenses
Description: This item represents the interest expense net of interest income.

Name: Net Interest Income (Bank)
Description: This item represents the interest income as it relates to banking and financial institutions.

Name: Net Interest Income After Provision For Loan Losses (Bank)
Description: This item represents the net interest income after provision for loan losses, as reported.

Name: Net Loans
Description: This item represents the net loans held by the banking and financial institution.

Name: Net Payout Yield
Description: A ratio that measures the cash dividend plus net stock repurchases over the trailing twelve months divided by the company's market capitalization.

Name: Net Rental Expense
Description: This item represents rental expenses incurred during the period covered by the financial statements on properties leased under operating leases.

Name: Net Working Capital
Description: Capital required to operate the day to day operations of a business. Calculated as (Total Current Assets - Cash & Short-term Investments) minus (Total Current Liabilities - Total Short-term Debt and Capital Leases - Dividends Payable)

Name: Net Working Capital Forecast
Description: Forecasted net working capital required to sustain operations.

Name: Net Working Capital Forecast Growth
Description: Period over prior period growth in forecasted net working capital required to sustain operations.

Name: Net Working Capital Forecast Margin
Description: Forecasted net working capital as percent of forecasted revenue.

Name: Net Working Capital Growth
Description: Period over prior period growth in net working capital.

Name: Net Working Capital Margin
Description: Net working capital expressed as a percent of revenue.

Name: Net-Net Working Capital (NNWC)
Description: A calculation inspired by Benjamin Graham. Net-Net Working Capital is calculated as (cash & short-term investments + 75% * accounts receivable + 50% * inventory) minus total liabilities.

Name: New Trading Ticker
Description: If applicable, new ticker symbol of trading item

Name: NI per SFAS 123 (after Options)
Description: This item represents the pro forma net income required to be disclosed as per SFAS No.123 which measures stock based compensation under fair value method.

Name: NNWC Per Share
Description: A calculation inspired by Benjamin Graham. Net-Net Working Capital is calculated as (cash & short-term investments + 75% * accounts receivable + 50% * inventory) minus total liabilities. NNWC per Shares expresses this calculation on per share basis.

Name: Non-Interest Bearing Deposits (Bank)
Description: This item represents non interest bearing deposits as relates to banks and financial institutions.

Name: Non Operating Income (Bank Expenses)
Description: The sum of all non-operating expenses for the given industry.

Name: Non-Cash Pension Expense
Description: The net amount of expenses paid for employee retirement benefits.

Name: NOPAT
Description: Net operating profit after tax (NOPAT) is calculated as operating income multiplied by 1 minus the tax rate: NOPAT = Operating Income x (1 - Tax Rate).

Name: NOPAT Forecast
Description: Projected net operating profit after tax.

Name: NOPAT Forecast CAGR (10y)
Description: Ten year compound annual growth rate in forecasted net operating profit after tax.

Name: NOPAT Forecast CAGR (5y)
Description: Five year compound annual growth rate in forecasted net operating profit after tax.

Name: NOPAT Forecast Growth
Description: Period over prior period growth in forecasted net operating profit after tax (NOPAT).

Name: NOPAT Forecast Margin
Description: Forecasted net operating profit after tax as a percent of forecasted revenue.

Name: Normalized Basic EPS
Description: This item is calculated as Normalized Net Income / Basic Weighted Average Shares Outstanding. This item is adjusted for historical stock splits and for multiple class companies, per share items are primary class equivalent, and for foreign companies listed as primary ADRs, per share items are ADR-equivalent.

Name: Normalized Diluted EPS
Description: This item is calculated as Normalized Net Income / Diluted Weighted Average Shares Outstanding. This item is adjusted for historical stock splits and for multiple class companies, per share items are primary class equivalent, and for foreign companies listed as primary ADRs, per share items are ADR-equivalent.

Name: Normalized Net Income
Description: This item is EBT, Excl. Unusual Items * (1 - Statutory Tax Rate) + Minority Int. in Earnings. Note: this metric assumes statutory tax rate of 37.5% for all companies.

Name: Number of Buy Recommendations
Description: The number of analysts publishing a Buy recommendation for the stock.

Name: Number of Hold Recommendations
Description: The number of analysts publishing a Hold recommendation for the stock.

Name: Number of No Opinion Recommendations
Description: The number of analysts publishing a No Opinion recommendation for the stock.

Name: Number of Outperform Recommendations
Description: The number of analysts publishing an Outperform recommendation for the stock.

Name: Number of Sell Recommendations
Description: The number of analysts publishing a Sell recommendation for the stock.

Name: Number of Underperform Recommendations
Description: The number of analysts publishing an Underperform recommendation for the stock.

Name: Operating Cash Flow Margin
Description: A ratio that measures the amount of revenue a firm can convert into operating cash flow.

Name: Operating Country
Description: Country name where the company primarily operates

Name: Operating Country ISO Code
Description: Three letter ISO Code of the country where the company primarily operates

Name: Operating Income
Description: The income after operating expenses.

Name: Operating Income CAGR (10y)
Description: Ten-year compound annual growth rate in operating income.

Name: Operating Income CAGR (3y)
Description: Three-year compound annual growth rate in operating income.

Name: Operating Income CAGR (5y)
Description: Five-year compound annual growth rate in operating income.

Name: Operating Income CAGR (7y)
Description: Seven-year compound annual growth rate in operating income.

Name: Operating Income Growth
Description: Period over prior period growth in operating income.

Name: Operating Income Margin
Description: Operating income expressed as a percent of revenue.

Name: Operating Income Margin CAGR (10y)
Description: Ten-year compound annual growth rate in operating income margin.

Name: Operating Income Margin CAGR (3y)
Description: Three-year compound annual growth rate in operating income margin.

Name: Operating Income Margin CAGR (5y)
Description: Five-year compound annual growth rate in operating income margin.

Name: Operating Income Margin CAGR (7y)
Description: Seven-year compound annual growth rate in operating income margin.

Name: Operating Leases, Debt Equivalent
Description: This item represents the amount of additional capital leases on the company's balance sheet if all operating leases were capitalized.

Name: Operating Region
Description: The operating region name of the company

Name: Operating Region ID
Description: The operating region id of the company

Name: Other Current Assets
Description: Field containing the sum of all current assets that cannot be standardized into another field as well as those that are aggregated by the company because materially, they are too small to list separately.

Name: Other Current Liabilities
Description: This item represents all residual data items that do not fit perfectly into any of the current liabilities categories separately categorized. If Other Current Liabilities are combined with accrued expenses or with any other liabilities, where Other Current Liabilities appear as first string and the company does not report the break up for the same, then the same will form part of this data item only.

Name: Other Financing Activities
Description: This item represents all other financing cash flows, not included in any specific data item.

Name: Other Intangibles
Description: This item represents the net values of those assets (i.e. gross intangibles less accumulated amortization), which provide future economic benefit to the enterprise but have no physical form. It also includes the combined net amount of "Goodwill and Intangibles" (i.e. gross goodwill and intangibles as reduced by the accumulated amortization), where it is not possible to separately identify net goodwill and net intangibles.

Name: Other Investing Activities
Description: This item represents all other investing cash flows not included in any specific data item.

Name: Other Long-Term Assets
Description: The sum of all assets classified as non-current

Name: Other Non Operating Income (Expenses)
Description: This item represents any other income (expense), which is not directly attributable to the operating activities of the company.

Name: Other Non-Current Liabilities
Description: Field containing the sum of all non-current liabilities that cannot be standardized into another field as well as those that are aggregated by the company because materially, they are too small to list separately.

Name: Other Operating Activities
Description: This item represents all other operating cash flows, not included in any specific data item.

Name: Other Operating Expenses, Total
Description: This item represents the other operating costs incurred during the given fiscal year.

Name: Other Operating Expenses (Income)
Description: This item represents all other operating expenses incurred in the ordinary course of business, which are recurring in nature. If company combines other income with other expense, then we do not include in this item.

Name: Other Payables
Description: Miscellaneous payables.

Name: Other Receivables
Description: This item represents all amounts receivable by the company in the form of cash other than those classified as accounts receivable or notes receivable.

Name: Other Revenue
Description: This item represents the incidental revenues that are earned while performing the primary activities of the company.

Name: Other Unusual Items
Description: This item represents any non-recurring income (expense) such as write off of inventories and note receivable, impairment of goodwill and any other special, unusual and one time income (expense).

Name: Other Unusual Items
Description: This item represents any the sum of all non-recurring income (expense) such as write off of inventories and note receivable, impairment of goodwill and any other special, unusual and one time income (expense).

Name: Owner Earnings
Description: A measure of free cash flow made famous by Warren Buffett when he wrote about it in Berkshire Hathaway's annual report in 1986. Mr. Buffett stated that the value of a company is the present value of owner earnings expected to occur over the life of a business, less any reinvestment of earnings.

Name: Owner Earnings Yield
Description: Measures amount of ower earnings for each dollar of market cap.

Name: P/E Ratio
Description: Indicates the multiple of earnings that stock investors are willing to pay for one share of the firm.

Name: P/E Ratio (Adjusted)
Description: Indicates the multiple of earnings, adjusted for usual items, that stock investors are willing to pay for one share of the firm.

Name: P/E Ratio (Fwd)
Description: Indicates the multiple of forward earnings that stock investors are willing to pay for one share of the firm.

Name: Payment Date of Last Dividend
Description: Date of the last dividend payment.

Name: Payment Type of Last Dividend
Description: Payment type of the last dividend. Value can be one of the following: cash, stock, spinoff, rights, and multiple dividends.

Name: Payout Ratio
Description: A ratio that measures the percentage of net income a firm is paying out to shareholders versus retaining for reinvestment in the business.

Name: Payout Ratio Forecast
Description: Projected payout ratio.

Name: PEG Ratio
Description: A heuristic used to measure the level of earnings growth reflected in a stock's market price.

Name: PEG Ratio Fwd
Description: A heuristic used to measure the level of projected earnings growth reflected in a stock's market price.

Name: Period End Date
Description: The date of the reporting period.

Name: Piotroski Score
Description: A score developed by Stanford accounting professor Joseph Piotroski to find companies with healthy Liquid Balance Sheets, Profitability, and Operating Efficiency.

Name: Policy Acq. And Underwriting Costs
Description: This item represents the policy acquisition costs including deferred costs of various types of insurance businesses.

Name: Policy Benefits
Description: This item represents the benefits/dividends paid or payable to policyholders including Life, Accident & Health, Property & Casualty and Annuity policyholders.

Name: Pre-tax Income Margin
Description: Earnings before taxes expressed as a percent of revenue.

Name: Pref. Stock, Non-Redeemable
Description: This item represents the preferred stock of the company which is not redeemable during its life time.

Name: Preferred Dividends Paid (CF)
Description: The sum of dividends paid to preferred and other equity holders.

Name: Preferred Dividends Paid CAGR (10y)
Description: Ten-year compound annual growth rate in preferred dividends paid.

Name: Preferred Dividends Paid CAGR (3y)
Description: Three-year compound annual growth rate in preferred dividends & other adj.

Name: Preferred Dividends Paid CAGR (5y)
Description: Five-year compound annual growth rate in preferred dividends & other adj.

Name: Preferred Dividends Paid CAGR (7y)
Description: Seven-year compound annual growth rate in preferred dividends & other adj.

Name: Preferred Dividends Paid Growth
Description: Period over prior period growth in preferred dividends & other adj.

Name: Preferred Dividends Paid Margin
Description: Preferred dividends & other adjustments expressed as a percent of revenue.

Name: Preferred Stock Redeemable
Description: Mandatorily redeemable securities of subsidiary companies.

Name: Prepaid Expenses
Description: A current asset created by prepayment of costs and expenses for which the benefits will occur at a future date.

Name: Price / Book
Description: Compares a firm's market value of equity to the amount of common equity listed on the balance sheet.

Name: Price / Fwd Sales
Description: Indicates the multiple of forward sales that stock investors are willing to pay for one share of the firm.

Name: Price / LTM Sales
Description: Indicates the multiple of sales that stock investors are willing to pay for one share of the firm.

Name: Price / NCAV
Description: Compares the current stock price to the Net Current Asset Value (NCAV) where NCAV equals the company's Current Assets minus its Total Liabilities.

Name: Price / NNWC
Description: Compares the current stock price to the Net Net Working Capital (NNWC) where NNWC equals Cash & Equivalents + (Accounts Receivables x 0.75) + (Inventory x 0.5) - Total Liabilities.

Name: Price / Operating Cash Flow
Description: Measures the ratio of a stock's price to its operating cash flow per share.

Name: Price / Tangible Book Value
Description: Compares a firm's market value of equity to its book value of tangible common equity value.

Name: Price $ Change Today
Description: The change in stock price so far today.

Name: Price % Change Today
Description: The percentage change in stock price so far today.

Name: Primary Ticker of Company
Description: The ticker of the primary trading item for the company.

Name: Primary Trading Item Flag
Description: Returns the value TRUE if the trading item is a Primary Ticker of Company

Name: Projected Pension Benefit Obligation
Description: Liabilities for employee post-retirement benefits.

Name: Projected Pension Benefit Obligation
Description: This item represents the total projected benefits, vested and non-vested payable by an employer to an employee in respect of defined benefit pension plans (Both Domestic and Foreign Plans).

Name: Property Plant And Equipment, Net
Description: The sum of all gross property, plant & equipment minus total accumulated depreciation and depletion.

Name: Quick Ratio
Description: A ratio used to assess a company's short-term liquidity.

Name: R&D Expenses
Description: An expense arising from studies and product development processes.

Name: Real Estate Owned
Description: Real estate and other properties reported separately from other plant, property and equipment fields.

Name: Record Date of Last Dividend
Description: Record date is the cut-off date used to determine which shareholders are entitled to receive a corporate dividend.

Name: Reinsurance Payable
Description: This item represents the premiums payable by an insurance company to another insurance company in respect of insurance ceded in order to reduce its overall risk.

Name: Reinsurance Recoverable
Description: This item represents amounts recoverable from other insurance companies (re-insurers) for claims paid which are covered by reinsurance. When insurance risk is ceded to other re-insuring companies, a portion of premiums is paid to them and if a claim arises, then a portion of the claim paid is recoverable from them as per the terms of the reinsurance contract. It also includes other amounts recoverable from reinsurers when reported by the company under the 'Reinsurance' section.

Name: Relative Strength Index (14d)
Description: A momentum oscillator that measures the speed and change of price movements.

Name: Reporting Currency
Description: The currency in which a company's reports its financial statements.

Name: Reporting Frequency
Description: The frequency with which a company's reports its financial statements.

Name: Reporting Scale
Description: The unit in which a company's reports its financial statements (thousands, millions, billions, etc.).

Name: Repurchase of Common Stock
Description: The amount of cash spent by the company to repurchase company stock in the given period.

Name: Research and Development CAGR (10y)
Description: Ten-year compound annual growth rate in research and development.

Name: Research and Development CAGR (3y)
Description: Three-year compound annual growth rate in research and development.

Name: Research and Development CAGR (5y)
Description: Five-year compound annual growth rate in research and development.

Name: Research and Development CAGR (7y)
Description: Seven-year compound annual growth rate in research and development.

Name: Research and Development Growth
Description: Period over prior period growth in research and development.

Name: Research and Development Margin
Description: The sum of research and development expenses as a percent of revenue.

Name: Restricted Cash
Description: This item represents cash and cash equivalents, which are restricted for use or transfer, and normally consists of funds held in escrow or cash restricted in use.

Name: Restructuring Charges
Description: Expenses incurred from reorganizing a company's internal operational architecture or debt structure.

Name: Retained Earnings
Description: Profits reinvested in the corporation after dividends have been paid out.

Name: Return on Assets
Description: A ratio that measures the dollars in net profit a business generates per dollar of assets it owns.

Name: Return on Assets CAGR (10y)
Description: Ten-year compound annual growth rate in return on assets.

Name: Return on Assets CAGR (3y)
Description: Three-year compound annual growth rate in return on assets.

Name: Return on Assets CAGR (5y)
Description: Five-year compound annual growth rate in return on assets.

Name: Return on Assets CAGR (7y)
Description: Seven-year compound annual growth rate in return on assets.

Name: Return on Capital
Description: This item is calculated as EBIT divided by the sum of (Total Equity + Total Debt + Total Deferred Tax Liabilities). If the denominator is less than or equal to zero then the ratio will be shown as NM and if the return is less than (300%) then the value will be shown as NM.

Name: Return On Capital Employed
Description: A capital efficiency ratio used to measure a firm's profitability relative to the capital employed. Capital employed is defined as total assets minus current liabilities.

Name: Return on Common Equity
Description: A ratio used to measure the return that a firm generates on the book value of common equity.

Name: Return on Equity CAGR (10y)
Description: Ten-year compound annual growth rate in return on equity.

Name: Return on Equity CAGR (3y)
Description: Three-year compound annual growth rate in return on equity.

Name: Return on Equity CAGR (5y)
Description: Five-year compound annual growth rate in return on equity.

Name: Return on Equity CAGR (7y)
Description: Seven-year compound annual growth rate in return on equity.

Name: Return on Invested Capital
Description: A capital efficiency ratio used to measure a firm's ability to create value for all its stakeholders, debt, and equity.

Name: Return on Invested Capital CAGR (10y)
Description: Ten-year compound annual growth rate in return on invested capital.

Name: Return on Invested Capital CAGR (3y)
Description: Three-year compound annual growth rate in return on invested capital.

Name: Return on Invested Capital CAGR (5y)
Description: Five-year compound annual growth rate in return on invested capital.

Name: Return on Invested Capital CAGR (7y)
Description: Seven-year compound annual growth rate in return on invested capital.

Name: Revenue
Description: The sum of all revenue fields included for a company's operating activities.

Name: Revenue CAGR (10y)
Description: Ten-year compound annual growth rate in revenue.

Name: Revenue CAGR (3y)
Description: Three-year compound annual growth rate in revenue.

Name: Revenue CAGR (5y)
Description: Five-year compound annual growth rate in revenue.

Name: Revenue CAGR (7y)
Description: Seven-year compound annual growth rate in revenue.

Name: Revenue Forecast
Description: Forecasted revenue based on consensus analyst estimates when available.

Name: Revenue Forecast CAGR (10y)
Description: Ten year compound annual growth rate in forecasted revenue.

Name: Revenue Forecast CAGR (5y)
Description: Five year compound annual growth rate in forecasted revenue.

Name: Revenue Forecast Consensus Standard Deviation
Description: Standard deviation in forecasted Revenue.

Name: Revenue Forecast Count of Estimates
Description: The number of analysts publishing a Revenue Forecast for the stock.

Name: Revenue Forecast High Consensus
Description: The highest Revenue Forecast submitted by any analyst for the company.

Name: Revenue Forecast Low Consensus
Description: The lowest Revenue Forecast submitted by any analyst for the company.

Name: Revenue Forecast Mean Consensus
Description: The mean or average Revenue Forecast submitted by any analyst for the company.

Name: Revenue Forecast Median Consensus
Description: The median Revenue Forecast submitted by any analyst for the company.

Name: Revenue Growth
Description: Period over prior period growth in revenue.

Name: Revenue Growth Forecast
Description: Period over prior period growth in forecasted revenue.

Name: Rule of 40
Description: A ratio that measures a companys combined growth rate and profit margin. Many venture capital and growth equity investors believe this ratio should exceed 40%, especially for software companies

Name: Salaries and Other Emply. Benefits
Description: This item represents the salaries and other benefits provided to the employees.

Name: Sale of Property, Plant and Equipment
Description: This item represents cash received (inflows) by the company from the sale of plant, property and equipment.

Name: Sector
Description: The sector in which a stock operates.

Name: Sector ID
Description: The unique sector id assigned to a company.

Name: Securities Purchased Under Agreements To Resell
Security End Date
Description: Last trading date of a delisted security.

Name: Security Features
Description: Special features associated with the security

Name: Security Name
Description: Name of trading item's security

Name: Security Start Date
Description: The date the subject security was issued

Name: Security Subtype
Description: Type of trading item's security

Name: Selling, General & Admin Expenses
Description: The sum of all selling, general and administrative expenses.

Name: Selling, General and Admin CAGR (10y)
Description: Ten-year compound annual growth rate in selling, general and administrative expenses.

Name: Selling, General and Admin CAGR (3y)
Description: Three-year compound annual growth rate in selling, general and administrative expenses.

Name: Selling, General and Admin CAGR (5y)
Description: Five-year compound annual growth rate in selling, general and administrative expenses.

Name: Selling, General and Admin CAGR (7y)
Description: Seven-year compound annual growth rate in selling, general and administrative expenses.

Name: Selling, General and Admin Growth
Description: Period over prior period growth in selling, general and administrative expenses.

Name: Selling, General and Admin Margin
Description: The sum of selling, general and administrative expenses as a percent of revenue.

Name: Shareholder Yield
Description: A ratio that measures the total amount of money the company is returning back to shareholders in the form of cash dividends, net stock repurchases, and debt paydown.

Name: Shares Outstanding
Description: Shares outstanding of company's equity shares

Name: Shares Outstanding Adjustment Factor
Description: The number of shares of the primary security that are represented by each trading security.

Name: Shares Outstanding CAGR (10y)
Description: Ten-year compound annual growth rate in shares outstanding.

Name: Shares Outstanding CAGR (3y)
Description: Three-year compound annual growth rate in shares outstanding.

Name: Shares Outstanding CAGR (5y)
Description: Five-year compound annual growth rate in shares outstanding.

Name: Shares Outstanding CAGR (7y)
Description: Seven-year compound annual growth rate in shares outstanding.

Name: Shares per Depository Receipt
Description: ADR/GDR ratio for all companies that are deemed the ADR/GDR security as company primary (all non-primary ADR/GDR companies will be given a value = 1)

Name: Short Interest (Shares)
Description: This item represents the number of shares that have been sold short but have not yet been covered or closed out.

Name: Short Interest Ratio
Description: The ratio of tradable shares being shorted to shares in the market.

Name: Short Term Debt Coverage Ratio
Description: A ratio that measures the amount of cash flow a firm generates for each dollar of short-term debt it uses

Name: Short Term Investments
Description: The aggregate value of debt and or equity investments with maturities or benefits lasting less than one year.

Name: Short-term Borrowings
Description: Amounts owed that are documented by printed notes.

Name: Short-Term Debt Issued
Description: This item represents cash inflows on account of issuance of short-term debt.

Name: Short-Term Debt Repaid
Description: This item represents cash outflows on account of repayment of short-term debt.

Name: Similar Companies
Description: Companies similar to the subject company.

Name: Similar Companies IDs
Description: Ids of companies that are similar to the subject company.

Name: Special Dividend Paid
Description: This item represents any special dividend/distribution to the equity shareholders apart from the normal dividend distribution. This type of dividend distribution is non-recurring in nature.

Name: Stock Exchange Code
Description: The primary stock exchange where a stock is listed.

Name: Stock Price (Current)
Description: The current stock price.

Name: Stock Price Close (Div & Split Adjusted)
Description: The stock price at the close of the last trading day.

Name: Stock Price Close (Div & Split Adjusted) (Trading Days Only)
Stock Price Close (Split Adjusted)
Description: The stock price at the close of the trading day.

Name: Stock Price Close Date
Description: The date of the stock price.

Name: Stock Price Close Date (Trading Days Only)
Stock Price High (Div & Split Adjusted) (Trading Days Only)
Stock Price Low (Div & Split Adjusted) (Trading Days Only)
Stock-Based Comp, SG&A Expense
Description: This item represents the stock based compensation included in SG&A when available.

Name: Stock-Based Comp
Description: Total Stock-Based Compensation is a supplemental line item with the following components: Stock-Based Comp., COGS (Total), Stock-Based Comp., R&D Exp. (Total), Stock-Based Comp., S&M Exp. (Total), Stock-Based Comp., G&A Exp. (Total), Stock-Based Comp., SG&A Exp. (Total), Stock-Based Comp., Other (Total), Stock-Based Comp., After-Tax (Total).

Name: Stock-Based Comp, Unallocated
Description: Stock-Based Comp., Other (Total) is a supplemental line item that represents stock based compensation disclosed by the company but not associated with a particular operating expense - values can be either main table line items or standalone values This item includes: Stock purchase discount Incentive stock and other compensation. ESOP expense Stock price related incentive program Stock appreciation right expense or stock discount Non-cash stock compensation Discretionary ESOP contribution Non-cash imputed (ESOP) compensation expense Contributions to employee profit sharing and employee stock option plan. Compensatory element of stock issuance Transaction related compensation charge. Non-recurring compensation expense on option grants. Share based plans.

Name: Tangible Book Value
Description: The book value of common equity less intangible assets.

Name: Tangible Book Value Per Share
Description: The book value of common equity less intangible assets on a per basic share basis.

Name: Tangible Common Equity
Description: The book value of common equity less intangible assets.

Name: Tangible Equity
Description: The book value of total equity less intangible assets.

Name: Ticker
Description: The ticker symbol a stock trades under on its primary stock exchange.

Name: Total Assets
Description: The sum of all assets on a company's balance sheet.

Name: Total Capital
Description: Total Capital is a supplemental line item with the following components: Total Preferred Equity, Total Debt, Total Common Equity, and Minority Interest, Total (Incl. Fin. Div).

Name: Total Capital (Market Value)
Description: Total Capital (Market Value) is a supplemental line item with the following components: Total Preferred Equity, Total Debt, Market Value of Total Common Equity, and Minority Interest, Total (Incl. Fin. Div).

Name: Cash And Short Term Investments
Description: Cash deposits at financial institutions that can immediately be withdrawn at any time, and investments maturing in one year or less that are highly liquid and therefore regarded as cash equivalents and reported with or near cash line items. Cash equivalents are extremely liquid investments with low risk that can immediately be converted to cash. Includes cash restricted for specific purposes.

Name: Common Equity
Description: The sum of all common equity items

Name: Common Equity CAGR (10y)
Description: Ten-year compound annual growth rate in total common equity.

Name: Common Equity CAGR (3y)
Description: Three-year compound annual growth rate in total common equity.

Name: Common Equity CAGR (5y)
Description: Five-year compound annual growth rate in total common equity.

Name: Common Equity CAGR (7y)
Description: Seven-year compound annual growth rate in total common equity.

Name: Total Current Assets
Description: The sum of all assets that are classified as current because they will provide a benefit within one year.

Name: Total Current Liabilities
Description: The sum of all liabilities classified as current for having maturities of less than one year.

Name: Current Taxes
Description: This item represents the current amount of income taxes payable, both domestic and foreign.

Name: Total Debt
Description: The sum of all debt and capital lease obligations.

Name: Total Debt / EBITDA
Description: A ratio that is calculated as Total Debt (including Capital Leases) divided by EBITDA.

Name: Total Debt / Total Capital
Description: A ratio that measures the level of the debt relative to the market value of total capital.

Name: Total Debt Issued
Description: This item is the sum of following components: Short Term Debt Issued, Long-Term Debt Issued, and Trust Preferred Securities Issued.

Name: Total Debt Repaid
Description: This item is the sum of following components: Capital Lease Payments, Trust Preferred Securities Repaid, Short Term Debt Repaid, and Long-Term Debt Repaid.

Name: Deferred Taxes
Description: This item represents the deferred amount of income taxes payable by the company, both domestic and foreign.

Name: Total Dividends Paid (Ex Special Dividends)
Description: This item represents cash outflows towards dividends or distributions, either to common or preferred stockholders during the relevant period. The amount paid may relate to pending dividend of earlier period also.

Name: Total Enterprise Value (TEV)
Description: The total value of a firm including claims of creditors (secured and unsecured) and shareholders (preferred and common). Unlikely Enterprise Value (EV), Total Enterprise Value includes value related to the non-operating assets of the business.

Name: Total Equity
Description: The sum of preferred and common equity items

Name: Total Liabilities
Description: The total value of all possible claims against the corporation.

Name: Total Liabilities / Total Assets
Description: A ratio that measures the proportion of a firm's assets financed by liabilities.

Name: Total Liabilities And Equity
Description: The total of all liabilities and shareholders' equity.

Name: Minority Interest, Total
Description: The book value of the reporting company's share of ownership in another company.

Name: Non-Interest Expense (Bank)
Description: This item represents the total non-interest expense, as reported.

Name: Non-Interest Income (Bank)
Description: This item represents the total non-interest income, as reported.

Name: Total Operating Expenses
Description: The sum of all operating expenses for the given industry.

Name: Other Non Interest Expense
Description: This item represents realized or unrealized Gains or Losses on Foreign exchange and reported by the company in the non-interest expense section, taxes other than income tax and all recurring operating expenses reported by the company in the non-interest expense section of Income Statement, other than salaries and other employee benefits, occupancy expense, equipment expenses, federal deposit insurance expense, stock-based compensation, selling general & administration expenses, amortization of goodwill and intangible assets, asset write-down, restructuring charges, loss on sale of loans, securities, assets and business, loss on foreclosed property, merger related charges etc.

Name: Other Non Interest Income
Description: This item represents income from loan origination and loan servicing activities, fee income from non-fund based activity like investment banking & capital market fees, brokerage fees, fees for other financial services, foreign exchange gains (losses) and all recurring operating incomes reported by the company in the non interest income section of Income Statement, other than service charges on deposits, trust income, income on foreclosed property, mortgage banking revenues, investment securities gains, trading account gain (loss), gain/loss on sale of loans, assets and business, credit card fee etc.

Name: Total Pension Plan Assets
Description: Assets for employee post-retirement benefits.

Name: Total Preferred Equity
Description: Preferred stock that is classified as a liability because of certain ownership and return criteria.

Name: Total Receivables
Description: This item represents the sum of: 1. Accounts Receivable - Trade, Accounts Receivable - Other, and Loans Receivable Current.

Name: Total Revenue (Insurance)
Description: This item represents the total revenue generated by the company. Adjusted for specific considerations for the Insurance industry.

Name: Trading Asset Securities
Description: This item represents both debt and equity securities, which reflect active and frequent buying and selling by the company with an intention to generate profits from short-term price movements. The main motto of investment is profit generation and not long-term holding or capital appreciation.

Name: Trading Country
Description: Trading country name of the trading item

Name: Trading Country ISO Code
Description: Trading country id (ISO 3-letter Code)

Name: Trading Currency
Description: The currency in which the security trades on the subject exchange.

Name: Trading Region
Description: The region of the exchange where the trading item trades.

Name: Trading to Reporting Currency FX Rate
Description: The foreign exchange rate between a security's trading currency and the company's reporting currency.

Name: Trading to Reporting Currency Pair
Description: The foreign exchange pair of security's trading currency and reporting currency.

Name: Trading Volume
Description: The amount of shares traded during the day.

Name: Trading Volume (Trading Days Only)
Description: The amount of shares traded during the day. Only returns data for trading days.

Name: Treasury Stock
Description: Common shares bought back by the issuing company and held in its treasury.

Name: Treasury Stock & Other
Description: Common shares bought back by the issuing company and held in its treasury and other equity.

Name: Trust Pref. Securities
Description: This item represents a specific type of security possessing characteristics of both equity and debt securities. A company creates trust-preferred security by creating a subsidiary trust and providing funds through loans to the parent company. The trust issues mandatory redeemable preferred securities and the proceeds are invested by the trust in the subordinated debentures of the company, which are the sole assets of the trust. On maturity the company repays the debentures and the Trust in turn use these amounts to redeem the preferred securities. The interest flows back through the subsidiary to the preferred shareholders. Because the interest paid to the trust is tax-deductible, and the subsidiary is not taxed on the interest received because it flows to the shareholders, the company may realize significant tax benefits.

Name: Unadjusted EBIT
Description: Income before interest and taxes

Name: Unadjusted EBIT CAGR (10y)
Description: Ten-year compound annual growth rate in unadjusted ebit.

Name: Unadjusted EBIT CAGR (3y)
Description: Three-year compound annual growth rate in EBIT.

Name: Unadjusted EBIT CAGR (5y)
Description: Five-year compound annual growth rate in EBIT.

Name: Unadjusted EBIT CAGR (7y)
Description: Seven-year compound annual growth rate in EBIT.

Name: Unadjusted EBIT Growth
Description: Period over prior period growth in EBIT.

Name: Unadjusted EBIT Margin
Description: Earnings before interest and taxes (EBIT) expressed as a percent of revenue.

Name: Unadjusted EBITDA
Description: Income before interest, taxes, depreciation and amortization.

Name: Unadjusted EBITDA CAGR (10y)
Description: Ten-year compound annual growth rate in unadjusted ebitda.

Name: Unadjusted EBITDA CAGR (3y)
Description: Three-year compound annual growth rate in unadjusted EBITDA.

Name: Unadjusted EBITDA CAGR (5y)
Description: Five-year compound annual growth rate in unadjusted EBITDA.

Name: Unadjusted EBITDA CAGR (7y)
Description: Seven-year compound annual growth rate in unadjusted EBITDA.

Name: Unadjusted EBITDA Growth
Description: Period over prior period growth in unadjusted EBITDA.

Name: Unadjusted EBITDA Margin
Description: Earnings before interest, taxes, depreciation and amortization (EBITDA) expressed as a percent of revenue.

Name: Unearned Revenue Current
Description: Revenue collected or promised for which the reporting company still has to provide goods or services less than 12 months into the future.

Name: Unearned Revenue Non Current
Description: Revenue collected or promised for which the reporting company still has to provide goods or services over 12 months into the future.

Name: Unfunded Proj. Benefit Obligation, Debt Equivalent
Description: This item represents the pre-tax debt equivalent of unfunded pension plans.

Name: Unlevered FCF Forecast
Description: Projected unlevered free cash flow.

Name: Unlevered FCF Forecast CAGR (10y)
Description: Ten year compound annual growth rate in forecasted unlevered free cash flow.

Name: Unlevered FCF Forecast CAGR (5y)
Description: Five year compound annual growth rate in forecasted unlevered free cash flow.

Name: Unlevered FCF Forecast Growth
Description: Period over prior period growth in forecasted unlevered free cash flow (UFCF).

Name: Unlevered FCF Forecast Margin
Description: Forecasted unlevered free cash flow as a percent of forecasted revenue.

Name: Unlevered Free Cash Flow
Description: A cash flow measure that represents cash available to all providers of capital, including debt, equity, and hybrid capital. It is used to remove the impact of capital structure on a firms value.

Name: Unlevered Free Cash Flow Growth
Description: Period over prior period growth in unlevered free cash flow.

Name: Unlevered Free Cash Flow Margin
Description: Unlevered free cash flow expressed as a percent of revenue.

Name: Unlevered Free Cash Flow Yield
Description: Measures amount of unlevered free cash flow for each dollar of enterprise value (when meaningful).

Name: Unlevered Return on Assets
Description: A ratio that measures the dollars in EBIT a business generates per dollar of assets it owns.

Name: Unusual Items
Description: Expense incurred for charges that are deemed to be special or non-recurring.

Name: Upside (Analyst Target)
Description: The percentage increase (if positive) or decrease (if negative) that professional analysts expect over the current stock price.

Name: WACC
Description: Our estimate of the weighted average cost of capital for a company.

Name: Weighted Average Basic Shares Out.
Description: The number of shares held by shareholders including insiders but not including a company's treasury shares, sourced from the company 10-K or 10-Q SEC reports.

Name: Weighted Average Diluted Shares Out.
Description: The number of shares held by shareholders including insiders but not including a company's treasury shares assuming conversion of all convertible debt, securities, warrants and options, sourced from the company 10-K or 10-Q SEC reports.

Name: Total Long-Term Liabilities
Description: The total value of all long term possible claims against the corporation.

Name: Stock Price, Previous Close
Description: The stock price at the close of the prior trading date.

Name: Debt / Equity, Adjusted
Description: A ratio that measures the level of the debt relative to the book value of common equity plus the absolute value of treasury stock.

Name: Chowder Rule Number
Description: A ratio that measures a companys combined growth rate and dividend yield. We calculate the Chowder Rule Number by adding the dividend yield plus five-year dividend CAGR.

Name: Chowder Rule Number (Fwd)
Description: A ratio that measures a companys combined growth rate and dividend yield. We calculate the forward Chowder Rule Number by adding the dividend yield plus five-year forecast net income CAGR.

Name: Other Adjustments to Net Income
Description: This item represents the deductions from net income other than preferred stock dividend, premium on redemption of preferred stock dividends, and other preferred stock related adjustments, which are considered in calculating basic earnings per share. Many companies show such adjustments in the income statement by way of a deduction from net income. Some times the company may not show the adjustments in income statement, instead, may report in the notes (calculation of Earnings per share). In such cases, it is brought from notes to financial statements.

Name: EPS Growth Forecast Count
Description: The number of analysts publishing a EPS Growth Forecast for the stock.

Name: EPS Growth Forecast High Consensus
Description: The highest EPS Growth Forecast submitted by any analyst for the company. The growth rate is calculated using the consensus actual estimate for the historic period. See "eps_actual" metric for more information.

Name: EPS Growth Forecast Low Consensus
Description: The lowest EPS Growth Forecast submitted by any analyst for the company. The growth rate is calculated using the consensus actual estimate for the historic period. See "eps_actual" metric for more information.

Name: EPS Growth Forecast Mean Consensus
Description: The mean or average EPS Growth Forecast submitted by any analyst for the company. The growth rate is calculated using the consensus actual estimate for the historic period. See "eps_actual" metric for more information.

Name: EPS Growth Forecast Median Consensus
Description: The median EPS Growth Forecast submitted by any analyst for the company. The growth rate is calculated using the consensus actual estimate for the historic period. See "eps_actual" metric for more information.

Name: Common Dividends Paid
Description: Since the "gross_divid" metric is sourced from the cash flow statement, the common dividends are not always reported by the company on a standalone basis (i.e., they're lumped in with the "total_div_paid_cf" metric). This metric solves for the cash outflow for dividends paid on a company's common stock by deducting "pref_div" from "total_div_paid_cf."

Name: Volume Weighted Average Price (VWAP)
Description: The Volume Weighted Average Price (VWAP) is the average price throughout the day, adjusted for volume of shares traded.

Name: Payout Ratio, Common
Description: A ratio that is calculated as common dividends paid divided by net income to common shareholders.

Name: EPS Forecast CAGR (10y)
Description: Ten year compound annual growth rate in forecasted earnings per share.

Name: EPS Forecast CAGR (5y)
Description: Five year compound annual growth rate in forecasted earnings per share.

Name: PEGY Ratio
Description: A heuristic used to measure the level of earnings growth and dividend yield reflected in a stock's market price.

Name: PEGY Ratio Fwd
Description: A heuristic used to measure the level of projected earnings growth and dividend yield reflected in a stock's market price.

Name: P/E Ratio (NTM)
Description: The multiple of forecast earnings for the next twelve months that stock investors are willing to pay for one share of the firm.

Name: FFO Payout Ratio (REIT)
Description: FFO payout ratio that is calculated as total dividends paid divided by funds from operations over the same period.

Name: AFFO Payout Ratio (REIT)
Description: AFFO payout ratio that is calculated as total dividends paid divided by adjusted funds from operations over the same period.

Name: Total Debt / FCF
Description: A ratio that is calculated as Total Debt (including Capital Leases) divided by levered free cash flow.

Name: Price / LTM FCF
Description: Measures the ratio of a stock's price to its levered free cash flow per share.

Name: Market Cap / LTM FFO
Description: Indicates the multiple of funds from operations (FFO) that stock investors are willing to pay for one share of the firm.

Name: Market Cap / Fwd FFO
Description: Indicates the multiple of projected funds from operations (FFO) that stock investors are willing to pay for one share of the firm.

Name: Market Cap / LTM AFFO
Description: Indicates the multiple of adjusted funds from operations (AFFO) that stock investors are willing to pay for one share of the firm.

Name: Market Cap / Fwd AFFO
Description: Indicates the multiple of projected adjusted funds from operations (AFFO) that stock investors are willing to pay for one share of the firm.

Name: Dividend Yield (Ex Special Dividends)
Description: Measures the cash returned to shareholders by a firm as a percentage of the price they pay for each share of stock.

Name: Last Earnings Date
Description: The date of the company announced earnings to the market

Name: AFFO Forecast Revision Date
Description: The date/time at which the current consensus estimate of forecasted AFFO was last updated.

Name: AFFO / Share Forecast Revision Date
Description: The date/time at which the current consensus estimate of forecasted AFFO per share was last updated.

Name: Capital Expenditures Forecast Revision Date
Description: The date/time at which the current consensus estimate of forecasted capital expenditures was last updated.

Name: Dividends Per Share Forecast Revision Date
Description: The date/time at which the current consensus estimate of forecasted dividend per share was last updated.

Name: Long Term Growth % Forecast Revision Date
Description: The date/time at which the current consensus estimate of forecasted long term growth was last updated.

Name: EBIT Forecast Revision Date
Description: The date/time at which the current consensus estimate of forecasted EBIT was last updated.

Name: EBITDA Forecast Revision Date
Description: The date/time at which the current consensus estimate of forecasted EBITDA was last updated.

Name: EPS Forecast Revision Date
Description: The date/time at which the current consensus estimate of forecasted EPS was last updated.

Name: FFO Forecast Revision Date
Description: The date/time at which the current consensus estimate of forecasted FFO was last updated.

Name: FFO / Share Forecast Revision Date
Description: The date/time at which the current consensus estimate of forecasted FFO per share was last updated.

Name: NAV Forecast Revision Date
Description: The date/time at which the current consensus estimate of forecasted NAV was last updated.

Name: NAV / Share Forecast Revision Date
Description: The date/time at which the current consensus estimate of forecasted NAV per share was last updated.

Name: Net Income Forecast Revision Date
Description: The date/time at which the current consensus estimate of forecasted net income was last updated.

Name: Revenue Forecast Revision Date
Description: The date/time at which the current consensus estimate of forecasted revenue was last updated.

Name: Sloan Ratio
Description: A formula developed by Richard Sloan in 1996 that measures the degree of accruals versus reported earnings.

Name: Degree of Operating Leverage (DOL)
Description: The degree of operating leverage measures the sensitivity of a company's operating income with respect to a change in revenue.

Name: Degree of Financial Leverage (DFL)
Description: The degree of financial leverage measures the sensitivity of a company's earnings per share to fluctuations in operating income, as a result of changes in its capital structure.

Name: Degree of Combined Leverage (DCL)
Description: The degree of combined leverage expands on the degree of operating leverage to provide a view of a company's ability to generate profits from sales. It multiplies DOL and DFL.

Name: 150 Day Moving Avg
Description: The average stock price over the last 150 trading days.

Name: Dividend Per Share (Ex Special Dividends)
Description: The dividend paid to shareholders for each share of stock. For quarterly dividend payers, it's common practice to multiply the most recent dividend by 4 to calculate dividend per share. Special dividends are not included in the calculation.

Name: Dividend Per Share (Ex Special Dividends & Split Unadjusted)
Description: The dividend paid to shareholders for each share of stock. For quarterly dividend payers, it's common practice to multiply the most recent dividend by 4 to calculate dividend per share. Special dividends are not included in the calculation and no adjustments are made for stock splits.

Name: Right-of-Use Assets
Description: The value of right of use (ROU) assets listed on the company's balance sheet. Also listed as operating lease assets by some companies.

Name: Amortization of Intangible Assets
Description: This item represents the amortization of intangible assets. The amortization returned by this data item reflects the amortization included in the depreciation and amortization used to calculate EBITDA.

Name: Next Earnings Date
Description: The next date that the company is expected to report earnings.

Name: Gains (Loss) on Currency Exchange
Description: This item represents any gain (loss) arises on exchanging one currency for another. Includes foreign currency fluctuation gains and losses; gain or (loss) from foreign currency forward contracts; gain or (loss) arising from translation of assets and liabilities; and denominated in foreign currencies to reporting currency

Name: Cash And ST Investments Growth
Description: Period over prior period growth in cash and short term investments.

Name: Avg Dividend Yield (10y)
Description: Ten-year quarterly average dividend yield.

Name: Avg Dividend Yield (5y)
Description: Five-year quarterly average dividend yield.

Name: Avg Dividend Yield (3y)
Description: Three-year quarterly average dividend yield.

Name: Median Dividend Yield (10y)
Description: Ten-year quarterly median dividend yield.

Name: Median Dividend Yield (5y)
Description: Five-year quarterly median dividend yield.

Name: Median Dividend Yield (3y)
Description: Three-year quarterly median dividend yield.

Name: Share Turnover Ratio
Description: This item represents three-month average volume divided by the shares outstanding for a company

Name: Corporate Tax Rate (Operating Country)
Description: Corporate tax rate in the country where the company operates.

Name: Equity Risk Premium (Operating Country)
Description: Equity risk premium in the country where the company operates as estimated by professor Aswath Damodaran at NYU Stern. Source: http://pages.stern.nyu.edu/~adamodar/New_Home_Page/datafile/ctryprem.html.

Name: Marginal Equity Risk Premium (Operating Country)
Description: Marginal equity risk premium in the country where the company operates over the U.S. equity risk premium as estimated by professor Aswath Damodaran at NYU Stern. Source: http://pages.stern.nyu.edu/~adamodar/New_Home_Page/datafile/ctryprem.html.

Name: Income from Equity Method Investments
Description: This item represents the investing company's share of earnings/loss from affiliates, unconsolidated subsidiaries, partnerships, joint ventures and any other investments, which are accounted for under Equity method.

Name: Revenue Forecast CAGR (2y)
Description: Two year compound annual growth rate in forecasted revenue.

Name: Revenue Forecast CAGR (3y)
Description: Three year compound annual growth rate in forecasted revenue.

Name: EBITDA Forecast CAGR (2y)
Description: Two year compound annual growth rate in forecasted ebitda.

Name: EBITDA Forecast CAGR (3y)
Description: Three year compound annual growth rate in forecasted ebitda.

Name: EBIT Forecast CAGR (2y)
Description: Two year compound annual growth rate in forecasted ebit.

Name: EBIT Forecast CAGR (3y)
Description: Three year compound annual growth rate in forecasted ebit.

Name: NOPAT Forecast CAGR (2y)
Description: Two year compound annual growth rate in forecasted NOPAT.

Name: NOPAT Forecast CAGR (3y)
Description: Three year compound annual growth rate in forecasted NOPAT.

Name: Unlevered FCF Forecast CAGR (2y)
Description: Two year compound annual growth rate in forecasted unlevered FCF.

Name: Unlevered FCF Forecast CAGR (3y)
Description: Three year compound annual growth rate in forecasted unlevered FCF.

Name: Net Income Forecast CAGR (2y)
Description: Two year compound annual growth rate in forecasted net income.

Name: Net Income Forecast CAGR (3y)
Description: Three year compound annual growth rate in forecasted net income.

Name: EPS Forecast CAGR (2y)
Description: Two year compound annual growth rate in forecasted EPS.

Name: EPS Forecast CAGR (3y)
Description: Three year compound annual growth rate in forecasted EPS.

Name: FFO Forecast CAGR (2y)
Description: Two year compound annual growth rate in forecasted funds from operations (FFO).

Name: FFO Forecast CAGR (3y)
Description: Three year compound annual growth rate in forecasted funds from operations (FFO).

Name: AFFO Forecast CAGR (2y)
Description: Two year compound annual growth rate in forecasted adjusted funds from operations (AFFO).

Name: AFFO Forecast CAGR (3y)
Description: Three year compound annual growth rate in forecasted adjusted funds from operations (AFFO).

Name: James Montier's C-score
Description: C-Score developed by James Montier is a score between 0-6 that attempts to identify companies that may be manipulating earnings or "cooking the books".

Name: Stock Price Standard Deviation (1 year)
Description: Standard deviation of closing price over the last one year.

Name: Realized Volatility (1y)
Description: Realized volatility (also known as rolling volatility) over the last one year.

Name: Realized Volatility (30d Annualized)
Description: Realized volatility (also known as rolling volatility) over the last 30 days.

Name: Realized Volatility (60d Annualized)
Description: Realized volatility (also known as rolling volatility) over the last 60 days.

Name: Realized Volatility (90d Annualized)
Description: Realized volatility (also known as rolling volatility) over the last 90 days.

Name: FCF / Net Income
Description: This data item measures the ratio of levered free cash flow to net income to common, excluding extra items. It is a quick and helpful check on the quality of earnings.

Name: Avg EPS Growth (3y)
Description: Three-year quarterly average growth in diluted EPS from continuing operations.

Name: Avg EPS Growth (5y)
Description: Five-year quarterly average growth in diluted EPS from continuing operations.

Name: Avg EPS Growth (7y)
Description: Seven-year quarterly average growth in diluted EPS from continuing operations.

Name: Avg EPS Growth (10y)
Description: Ten-year quarterly average growth in diluted EPS from continuing operations.

Name: Price / Cash & ST Investments
Description: Compares a firm's market value of equity to the amount of cash and short term investments listed on the balance sheet.

Name: Avg Price / Cash & ST Investments (10y)
Description: Ten-year quarterly average Price / Cash & ST Investments also known as Market Cap / Cash & ST Investments.

Name: Avg Price / Cash & ST Investments (5y)
Description: Five-year quarterly average Price / Cash & ST Investments also known as Market Cap / Cash & ST Investments.

Name: Gross Profit / Total Assets
Description: A ratio that measures the amount of gross profit the company generates as a percentage of total assets.

Name: Equity / Total Assets
Description: A ratio that measures a company's book value of total equity as a percentage of total assets.

Name: Cash And ST Investments / Total Assets
Description: A ratio that measures a company's cash and short-term investments as a percentage of total assets.

Name: Total Debt / Total Assets
Description: A ratio that measures a company's total debt as a percentage of total assets.

Name: Trading Region Id
Description: The region id of the exchange where the trading item trades.

Name: Net Debt / Equity
Description: A ratio that measures the level of the net debt relative to the book value of common equity. This ratio is also called net gearing ratio.

Name: Levered FCF CAGR (3y)
Description: Three-year compound annual growth rate in levered free cash flow.

Name: Levered FCF CAGR (5y)
Description: Five-year compound annual growth rate in levered free cash flow.

Name: Levered FCF CAGR (7y)
Description: Seven-year compound annual growth rate in levered free cash flow.

Name: Levered FCF CAGR (10y)
Description: Ten-year compound annual growth rate in levered free cash flow.

Name: Cash Amount of Upcoming Dividend
Description: Upcoming Cash dividend amount on a per-share basis.

Name: Cash Amount of Upcoming Dividend (Split Adj)
Description: Upcoming Cash dividend amount on a per-share basis, adjusted for stock splits.

Name: Ex-Date of Upcoming Dividend
Description: Upcoming ex-dividend date is usually two business days before the dividend record date. Shares purchased on or after the ex-dividend date are not eligible to receive the next dividend payment.

Name: Payment Date of Upcoming Dividend
Description: Upcoming date of the dividend payment.

Name: Payment Type of Upcoming Dividend
Description: Upcoming payment type of dividend. Value can be one of the following: cash, stock, spinoff, rights, and multiple dividends.

Name: Record Date of Upcoming Dividend
Description: Upcoming record date is the cut-off date used to determine which shareholders are entitled to receive a corporate dividend.

Name: Comps Fair Value
Description: Our estimate of fair value for a company using various comparable company analyses methods.

Name: Comps Fair Value Upside
Description: Our estimate of fair value upside for a company using various comparable company analyses methods.

Name: EPV Fair Value
Description: Our estimate of fair value for a company using earnings power value method.

Name: EPV Fair Value Upside
Description: Our estimate of fair value upside for a company using earnings power value method.

Name: DCF Fair Value
Description: Our estimate of fair value for a company using various discounted cash flow analysis methods.

Name: DCF Fair Value Upside
Description: Our estimate of fair value upside for a company using various discounted cash flow analysis methods.

Name: DDM Fair Value
Description: Our estimate of fair value for a company using various dividend discount models.

Name: DDM Fair Value Upside
Description: Our estimate of fair value upside for a company using various dividend discount models.

Name: Avg Return on Invested Capital (2y)
Description: Two-year quarterly average return on invested capital.

Name: Avg Return on Invested Capital Growth (2y)
Description: Growth in two-year quarterly average return on invested capital.

Name: Avg Return on Common Equity (2y)
Description: Two-year quarterly average return on common equity.

Name: Avg Return on Common Equity Growth (2y)
Description: Growth in two-year quarterly average return on common equity.

Name: Avg Return on Assets (2y)
Description: Two-year quarterly average return on assets.

Name: Avg Return on Assets Growth (2y)
Description: Growth in two-year quarterly average return on assets.

Name: P/S % of 3 Year Avg P/S
Description: Price / LTM Sales as a percentage of three-year quarterly average.

Name: P/E % of 3 Year Avg P/E
Description: Price / LTM EPS as a percentage of three-year quarterly average.

Name: P/B % of 3 Year Avg P/B
Description: Price / Book as a percentage of three-year quarterly average.

Name: Revenue Trend Score
Description: Trend score is calculated as the percentage of quarters within the past two years that had positive year-over-year revenue growth. When a quarterly growth value is not available, the denominator is adjusted accordingly. If a minimum of four quarters of data is not available, the value is returned as NA.

Name: Gross Profit Trend Score
Description: Trend score is calculated as the percentage of quarters within the past two years that had positive year-over-year gross profit growth. When a quarterly growth value is not available, the denominator is adjusted accordingly. If a minimum of four quarters of data is not available, the value is returned as NA.

Name: Operating Income Trend Score
Description: Trend score is calculated as the percentage of quarters within the past two years that had positive year-over-year operating income growth. When a quarterly growth value is not available, the denominator is adjusted accordingly. If a minimum of four quarters of data is not available, the value is returned as NA.

Name: EPS Trend Score
Description: Trend score is calculated as the percentage of quarters within the past two years that had positive year-over-year EPS growth. When a quarterly growth value is not available, the denominator is adjusted accordingly. If a minimum of four quarters of data is not available, the value is returned as NA.

Name: Total Debt Trend Score
Description: Trend score is calculated as the percentage of quarters within the past two years that had positive year-over-year total debt growth. When a quarterly growth value is not available, the denominator is adjusted accordingly. If a minimum of four quarters of data is not available, the value is returned as NA.

Name: FCF Levered Trend Score
Description: Trend score is calculated as the percentage of quarters within the past two years that had positive year-over-year levered free cash flow growth. When a quarterly growth value is not available, the denominator is adjusted accordingly. If a minimum of four quarters of data is not available, the value is returned as NA.

Name: Total Debt Growth
Description: Period over prior period growth in total debt.

Name: Revenue Cumulative Growth (3y)
Description: Cumulative revenue growth over the last three years

Name: Revenue Cumulative Growth (5y)
Description: Cumulative revenue growth over the last five years

Name: Gross Profit Cumulative Growth (3y)
Description: Cumulative gross profit growth over the last three years

Name: Gross Profit Cumulative Growth (5y)
Description: Cumulative gross profit growth over the last five years

Name: Operating Income Cumulative Growth (3y)
Description: Cumulative operating income growth over the last three years

Name: Operating Income Cumulative Growth (5y)
Description: Cumulative operating income growth over the last five years

Name: EPS Diluted Cumulative Growth (3y)
Description: Cumulative diluted EPS growth over the last three years

Name: EPS Diluted Cumulative Growth (5y)
Description: Cumulative diluted EPS growth over the last five years

Name: Total Debt Cumulative Growth (3y)
Description: Cumulative total debt growth over the last three years

Name: Total Debt Cumulative Growth (5y)
Description: Cumulative total debt growth over the last five years

Name: FCF Levered Cumulative Growth (3y)
Description: Cumulative levered free cash flow growth over the last three years

Name: FCF Levered Cumulative Growth (5y)
Description: Cumulative levered free cash flow growth over the last five years

Name: Revenue Growth (Quarterly)
Description: Quarterly period over quarterly prior period growth in revenue.

Name: Diluted EPS Growth (Quarterly)
Description: Quarterly period over quarterly prior period growth in diluted EPS.

Name: Avg Owner Earnings (5y)
Description: Five-year fiscal year average of owner earnings.

Name: Avg Owner Earnings (10y)
Description: Ten-year fiscal year average of owner earnings.

Name: Predicted EV / LTM Revenue
Description: Our estimate of the fair value EV / LTM Revenue for a company.

Name: Predicted EV / Fwd Revenue (FY+2)
Description: Our estimate of the fair value EV / Fwd Revenue (FY+2) for a company.

Name: Predicted EV / LTM EBITDA
Description: Our estimate of the fair value EV / LTM EBITDA for a company.

Name: Predicted EV / Fwd EBITDA (FY+2)
Description: Our estimate of the fair value EV / Fwd EBITDA (FY+2) for a company.

Name: Predicted EV / LTM EBIT
Description: Our estimate of the fair value EV / LTM EBIT for a company.

Name: Predicted EV / Fwd EBIT (FY+2)
Description: Our estimate of the fair value EV / Fwd EBIT (FY+2) for a company.

Name: Predicted P/E Ratio
Description: Our estimate of the fair value P/E Ratio for a company.

Name: Predicted Fwd P/E Ratio (FY+2)
Description: Our estimate of the fair value Fwd P/E Ratio (FY+2) for a company.
