Name: Predicted Price / LTM Sales Ratio
Description: Our estimate of the fair value Price / LTM Sales Ratio for a company.

Name: Predicted Price / Fwd Sales Ratio (FY+2)
Description: Our estimate of the fair value Price / Fwd Sales Ratio (FY+2) for a company.

Name: Predicted Price / Book
Description: Our estimate of the fair value Price / Book for a company.

Name: Predicted Market Cap / LTM FFO
Description: Our estimate of the fair value Market Cap / LTM FFO for a REIT.

Name: Predicted Market Cap / Fwd FFO (FY+2)
Description: Our estimate of the fair value Market Cap / Fwd FFO (FY+2) for a REIT.

Name: Predicted Market Cap / LTM AFFO
Description: Our estimate of the fair value Market Cap / LTM AFFO for a REIT.

Name: Predicted Market Cap / Fwd AFFO (FY+2)
Description: Our estimate of the fair value Market Cap / Fwd AFFO (FY+2) for a REIT.

Name: Predicted EV / Revenue Exit Multiple (FY+5)
Description: Our estimate of the fair value EV / Revenue Exit Multiple (FY+5) for a company.

Name: Predicted EV / Revenue Exit Multiple (FY+10)
Description: Our estimate of the fair value EV / Revenue Exit Multiple (FY+10) for a company.

Name: Predicted EV / EBITDA Exit Multiple (FY+5)
Description: Our estimate of the fair value EV / EBITDA Exit Multiple (FY+5) for a company.

Name: Predicted EV / EBITDA Exit Multiple (FY+10)
Description: Our estimate of the fair value EV / EBITDA Exit Multiple (FY+10) for a company.

Name: Predicted EV Growth Exit Rate (FY+5)
Description: Our estimate of the fair value EV Growth Exit Rate (FY+5) for a company.

Name: Predicted EV Growth Exit Rate (FY+10)
Description: Our estimate of the fair value EV Growth Exit Rate (FY+10) for a company.

Name: Last Trade Date
Description: Timestamp of last trade date.

Name: Stock Price Open (Div & Split Adjusted) (Trading Days Only)
Description: The trading day's adjusted opening stock price. Only returns data for trading days.

Name: Stock Exchange Name
Description: Name of stock exchange where the trading item trades.

Name: 15 Day Moving Avg
Description: The average stock price over the last 15 trading days.

Name: 7 Day Moving Avg
Description: The average stock price over the last 7 trading days.

Name: 9 Day Moving Avg
Description: The average stock price over the last 9 trading days.

Name: EV / EBITA
Description: Measures the dollars in Enterprise Value for each dollar of EBITA over the last twelve months.

Name: Avg Price / LTM FCF (5y)
Description: Five-year quarterly average P/FCF ratio.

Name: Avg Price / LTM FCF (10y)
Description: Ten-year quarterly average P/FCF ratio.

Name: EV / Revenue Growth Ratio
Description: A heuristic used to measure the level of revenue growth relative to the EV / Revenue multiple.

Name: EV / EBITDA Growth Ratio
Description: A heuristic used to measure the level of EBITDA growth relative to the EV / EBITDA multiple.

Name: EV / EBIT Growth Ratio
Description: A heuristic used to measure the level of EBIT growth relative to the EV / EBIT multiple.

Name: EV / IC Growth Ratio
Description: A heuristic used to measure the level of revenue growth relative to the EV / Invested Capital multiple.

Name: PB ROE Ratio
Description: A heuristic used to measure the level of return on equity relative to the Price / Book multiple.

Name: Price / Sales Growth Ratio
Description: A heuristic used to measure the level of revenue growth relative to the Price / Sales multiple.

Name: Price / FCF Growth Ratio
Description: A heuristic used to measure the level of revenue growth relative to the Price / FCF multiple.

Name: Price / OCF Growth Ratio
Description: A heuristic used to measure the level of revenue growth relative to the Price / OCF multiple.

Name: Cost of Revenues
Description: This expense item reflects the direct costs associated with revenues including cost of goods sold.

Name: Economic Risk Region
Description: The economic region of the country in which the company operates. Economic risk region is one of the following values: Developed, Frontier and Developing.

Name: Financial Health Growth Score
Description: Our proprietary growth score is one of the five components used in our financial health analysis. Growth score values range between 0 to 5 and roughly translate to a company's percentile ranking in its sector and economic risk region. For example, a growth score of 2 suggests the company's growth ranks in the 40th percentile in its sector and economic risk region.

Name: Financial Health Growth Grade
Description: Our proprietary growth grade is one of the five components used in our financial health analysis. Growth grades range between A to F and roughly translate to a company's percentile ranking in its sector and economic risk region. For example, a growth grade of B suggests the company's growth ranks between the 60th to 80th percentile in its sector and economic risk region.

Name: Financial Health Profit Score
Description: Our proprietary profit score is one of the five components used in our financial health analysis. Profit score values range between 0 to 5 and roughly translate to a company's percentile ranking in its sector and economic risk region. For example, a profit score of 2 suggests the company's profit ranks in the 40th percentile in its sector and economic risk region.

Name: Financial Health Profit Grade
Description: Our proprietary profit grade is one of the five components used in our financial health analysis. Profit grades range between A to F and roughly translate to a company's percentile ranking in its sector and economic risk region. For example, a profit grade of B suggests the company's profit ranks between the 60th to 80th percentile in its sector and economic risk region.

Name: Financial Health Price Momentum Score
Description: Our proprietary price momentum score is one of the five components used in our financial health analysis. Price momentum score values range between 0 to 5 and roughly translate to a company's percentile ranking in its sector and economic risk region. For example, a price momentum score of 2 suggests the company's price momentum ranks in the 40th percentile in its sector and economic risk region.

Name: Financial Health Price Momentum Grade
Description: Our proprietary price momentum grade is one of the five components used in our financial health analysis. Price momentum grades range between A to F and roughly translate to a company's percentile ranking in its sector and economic risk region. For example, a price momentum grade of B suggests the company's price momentum ranks between the 60th to 80th percentile in its sector and economic risk region.

Name: Financial Health Cash Flow Score
Description: Our proprietary cash flow score is one of the five components used in our financial health analysis. Cash flow score values range between 0 to 5 and roughly translate to a company's percentile ranking in its sector and economic risk region. For example, a cash flow score of 2 suggests the company's cash flow ranks in the 40th percentile in its sector and economic risk region.

Name: Financial Health Cash Flow Grade
Description: Our proprietary cash flow grade is one of the five components used in our financial health analysis. Cash flow grades range between A to F and roughly translate to a company's percentile ranking in its sector and economic risk region. For example, a cash flow grade of B suggests the company's cash flow ranks between the 60th to 80th percentile in its sector and economic risk region.

Name: Financial Health Relative Value Score
Description: Our proprietary relative value score is one of the five components used in our financial health analysis. Relative value score values range between 0 to 5 and roughly translate to a company's percentile ranking in its sector and economic risk region. For example, a relative value score of 2 suggests the company's relative value ranks in the 40th percentile in its sector and economic risk region.

Name: Financial Health Relative Value Grade
Description: Our proprietary relative value grade is one of the five components used in our financial health analysis. Relative value grades range between A to F and roughly translate to a company's percentile ranking in its sector and economic risk region. For example, a relative value grade of B suggests the company's relative value ranks between the 60th to 80th percentile in its sector and economic risk region.

Name: Financial Health Overall Score
Description: Our proprietary overall financial health score is the conclusion drawn from the five components used in our financial health analysis. Financial health score values range between 0 to 5 and very roughly translate to a company's percentile ranking in its sector and economic risk region.

Name: Financial Health Overall Grade
Description: Our proprietary overall financial health grade is the conclusion drawn from the five components used in our financial health analysis. Financial health grades range between A to F and very roughly translate to a company's percentile ranking in its sector and economic risk region.

Name: Financial Health Overall Label
Description: Our proprietary overall financial health label is the conclusion drawn from the five components used in our financial health analysis. Possible values for financial health grades are EXCELLENT, GREAT, GOOD, FAIR, and WEAK.

Name: Avg Pre-tax Income Margin (10y)
Description: Ten-year quarterly average pre-tax margin.

Name: Avg Pre-tax Income Margin (5y)
Description: Five-year quarterly average pre-tax margin.

Name: Revenue Per Share
Description: Total revenue on a per common share basis.

Name: Cash Per Share
Description: Cash and equivalents on a per common share basis.

Name: Operating Cash Flow Per Share
Description: Operating cash flow on a per common share basis.

Name: Capital Expenditures CAGR (3y)
Description: Ten-year compound annual growth rate in capital expenditures.

Name: Capital Expenditures CAGR (5y)
Description: Three-year compound annual growth rate in capital expenditures.

Name: Capital Expenditures CAGR (7y)
Description: Five-year compound annual growth rate in capital expenditures.

Name: Capital Expenditures CAGR (10y)
Description: Seven-year compound annual growth rate in capital expenditures.

Name: Long-term Debt / Equity
Description: A ratio that measures the level of the long-term debt relative to the book value of common equity.

Name: Return on Equity
Description: A ratio used to measure the return that a firm generates on the book value of total equity.

Name: Revenue Per Employee
Description: A ratio used to measure the revenue that a firm generates per employee.

Name: Net Income Per Employee
Description: A ratio used to measure the net income that a firm generates per employee.

Name: Debt / Total Equity
Description: A ratio that measures the level of the debt relative to the book value of total equity.

Name: Receivables Turnover
Description: A ratio used to measure how quickly a company is able to collect on its accounts receivable as compared to revenue.

Name: Avg Operating Cash Flow Margin (10y)
Description: Ten-year quarterly average operating cash flow margin.

Name: Avg Operating Cash Flow Margin (5y)
Description: Five-year quarterly average operating cash flow margin.

Name: Avg Levered FCF Margin (10y)
Description: Ten-year quarterly average levered free cash flow margin.

Name: Avg Levered FCF Margin (5y)
Description: Five-year quarterly average levered free cash flow margin.

Name: EBITDA Per Share
Description: EBITDA on a per common share basis.

Name: Free Cash Flow Per Share
Description: Levered free cash flow on a per common share basis.

Name: Revenue Per Share CAGR (3y)
Description: Three-year compound annual growth rate in revenue per share.

Name: Revenue Per Share CAGR (5y)
Description: Five-year compound annual growth rate in revenue per share.

Name: Revenue Per Share CAGR (7y)
Description: Seven-year compound annual growth rate in revenue per share.

Name: Revenue Per Share CAGR (10y)
Description: Ten-year compound annual growth rate in revenue per share.

Name: Book Value Per Share CAGR (3y)
Description: Three-year compound annual growth rate in book value per share.

Name: Book Value Per Share CAGR (5y)
Description: Five-year compound annual growth rate in book value per share.

Name: Book Value Per Share CAGR (7y)
Description: Seven-year compound annual growth rate in book value per share.

Name: Book Value Per Share CAGR (10y)
Description: Ten-year compound annual growth rate in book value per share.

Name: Cash from Operations CAGR (3y)
Description: Three-year compound annual growth rate in cash from operations.

Name: Cash from Operations CAGR (5y)
Description: Five-year compound annual growth rate in cash from operations.

Name: Cash from Operations CAGR (7y)
Description: Seven-year compound annual growth rate in cash from operations.

Name: Cash from Operations CAGR (10y)
Description: Ten-year compound annual growth rate in cash from operations.

Name: EBITDA CAGR (5y Interim)
Description: Five-year compound annual growth rate in EBITDA including the latest quarter.

Name: Avg Common Dividends (5y)
Description: Five-year fiscal year average of common dividends paid.
